Commentary: JAFFA FIRST UP! Woahhhhh! What a delivery to begin from Shaheen Afridi. Cracker. Afridi serves a back-of-a-length delivery, around off, it lands and nips away beautifully. Shadman Islam looks to defend but gets squared up as the ball whistles past the outside edge to the keeper.
Better from Islam. This is bowled slightly straighter and Islam defends it out.
Outside off, on a length, some away movement again and Islam misses his defensive push away.
A bumper this time, on middle and leg, Islam ducks down and lets it be.

Play and a miss! The fourth stump line is working out for Afridi. It is bowled on a length and it straightens off the seam, Islam looks to have a poke but misses. A smile on Shaheen's face. He is already smelling blood.
Maiden for Afridi! Fuller, but way outside off, moves away as Islam leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off, easily left alone by Saif.
Again, on a length and outside off, Saif does not want to fiddle with this and makes a leave.
FOUR! Bangladesh and Saif Hassan start with a boundary. Hasan Ali serves this on the pad, on a length, Saif Hassan just has to clip this gently and the ball speeds away to the fine leg boundary.
On a length, on middle, Hassan looks to tuck but gets a leading edge to the off side.
FOUR! Another boundary. Saif Hassan has begun well here with two boundaries. Too straight this time, on middle and leg, gently nudged to the fine leg fence.
On middle, pushed away to the leg side. 8 off Ali's first over!
Way outside off, an easy leave for Islam.
Short of a length, around off, tapped to point.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line, the ball lands and jags away slightly. Again, Shadman Islam misses his poke and the ball steams past his outside edge to the keeper.
Shadman Islam gets underway. Outside off, steered through point for a single.
Fuller, outside off, Hassan makes a leave.
Around off, on a length, pushed through mid off for one.
On off, Hassan plays this through point for one.
Good-length ball, on off, played towards covers.

FOUR! That looked so good. Islam's confidence will be given a boost due to this. Outside off, on a length, Shadman Islam presses forward and eases this through mid off. A player gives it chase but the ball wins the race.
Outside off, left alone.

Loud shot for LBW but turned down! Around off and middle, on a length, the ball jags back in this time, Islam misses his flick and is pinged on the pad. An appeal but the umpire says no. A discussion between Hasan Ali, Mohammad Rizwan, and Babar Azam but they do not take the review.
Bowled in the fourth stump line, an easy leave for Islam.
Good delivery again from Shaheen. Short of a length, around off, the ball lands and jags away and bounces a tad more too. Misses the outside edge of Hassan.
FOUR! Confident stroke from Hassan. This is pitched up by Afridi, around off, Saif Hassan plays this gently through covers and bags a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! That was a snorter of the delivery and Pakistan get their first wicket early on. Shaheen Afridi has been troubling the openers so far and his hard work has paid off. He sticks with the back-of-a-length delivery again, it is bowled around off and the ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Saif Hassan gets his blade high up, looking to defend it, but the ball catches the shoulder of the bat and loops up near short leg. Abid Ali has the easiest of takes and Pakistan send back one of Bangladesh's openers.
Howout: c Abid Ali b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Down the leg side, left alone.
FOUR! That is quite a way to open your account. Shaheen Afridi errs this time and bowls it on the pads, Najmul Hossain Shanto whips this one wonderfully through square leg and fetches a boundary.
Way outside off, slightly shorter, left alone.
Around off, kept out by Islam.
FOUR! The boundaries are coming by nicely for the hosts. A touch shorter this time, around off, Shadman Islam stands tall and powers this one through mid-wicket. Boundary.
Around off, defended out solidly.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
On middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
On the off pole, on a length, Shanto looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto his pad.

Short of a length, on the fifth stump channel, Shadman Islam defends inside the line and misses. An appeal from the slip cordon. Don't really know for what, since there was a big, big gap between bat and ball.

EDGY FOUR! Bangladesh just keep scoring the boundaries here. Outside off, on a good length, Shadman Islam wants to defend but gets squared up. The outside edge is induced and the ball sneaks through between gully and the slip cordon to the ropes.
Shadman Islam has just blocked that from his crease.
Down the leg side, the flick is missed.
Short of a length, on off, SI keeps it out.
Outside off, Islam raises his blade and lets the cherry pass.
Good inward movement, on off. Shanto presses forward and defends.
Length ball, around off, coming back in. Najmul Hossain Shanto watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Good-length ball, on off, nipping back in at 133.5 kph. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks this one to the off side.
On a length, on leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto works it to square leg for a single.
Around off, Shadman Islam defends this one without any trouble.

OUT! LBW! Good-length ball, around off and middle, coming back in sharply. Shadman Islam looks to work it on the leg side but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Hasan Ali appeals for LBW and the umpire straightaway raises his dreaded finger. Shadman Islam consults his partner and ultimately takes the review. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows all three reds and Shadman Islam has to walk back to the pavilion and the hosts lose a review too. Both the openers are back in the hut and Pakistan have started well, getting two wickets early.
On a length, going down the leg side. Najmul Hossain Shanto misses his flick.
On a length around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes it towards covers.
Fuller in length, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it back to the bowler who stops the ball on his followthrough.
Short ball from Shaheen Afridi this time, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks underneath.
A touch fuller, on leg. Shanto works it to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller, on off. Haque pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Shanto lets it sail through.
Full and on middle and leg, Shanto defends it on the leg side.
On a length, on off. Shanto gets behind the line of the ball and knocks it back to the bowler.
On off, Shanto blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Shanto pushes it towards short extra cover.

Fuller in length, on middle and leg, nipping back in. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. A fielder gives it a chase and manages to save the boundary as he pushes the ball back in right in time. Three runs taken.
Length ball, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it but finds the extra cover fielder.

JAFFA! What a beautiful delivery! Good-length ball, nipping away from the left-hander, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets all squared up as he tries to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller in length, on off. Shanto pushes it to short extra cover.
Full again, outside off. Shanto leaves it alone.
A maiden to begin with for Faheem Ashraf! Good-length ball, on off. Shanto prods and blocks it towards covers.

NOT OUT! Tosses it up nicely, on middle and leg. Mominul Haque presses forward and looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Sajid Khan pleads the umpire for lbw but he is not interested. Pakistan and Co. discuss and they opt for a review at the last second. UltraEdge says that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing as the ball was going down the leg side. Pakistan lose their review.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Mominul Haque rocks back and cuts it through covers for a couple of runs.
Loopy ball, on middle. Haque blocks it out.
Floats it up, on middle. Haque clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full and on leg, Shanto defends it on the leg side.
Full and outside off, Haque shoulders arms to that one.
On a length, around off. Haque leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. Haque lets it be.
Short ball from Ashraf this time, on middle. Mominul Haque ducks and evades it with ease.
Short of a length, outside off, angling away, Mominul Haque leaves it for the keeper to collect.

Nice shot! Fuller and straighter, on middle. Mominul Haque covers the line, presents the full face of the bat, and drives it past the bowler. Shaheen Afridi gives it a chase and parries it back to the other fielder. Three runs taken.
Loopy ball, outside off, some extra bounce there. Mominul Haque looks to cut but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slower and angling in, Haque defends it with soft hands.
Tosses it up, outside off. Haque defends it on the off side.
Flatter and fuller, on off. Haque presses forward and blocks.
Flatter ball, angling in middle and leg. Haque gets a good stride forward and defends it out.
A maiden for Sajid Khan! Slider which skids on, Haque brings out his bat in time and blocks this one out.
FOUR! Super shot. On a fuller length, just around the off pole, Najmul Hossain Shanto presents the full face of the blade and creams this through mid off for a boundary.
Around off, pushed to the leg side.
Fuller, slightly outside off, Shanto gets his front foot ahead and leaves it.
Good-length delivery, on off, defended out well.
Back of a length, around off, kept out nicely by Shanto.
Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes this length delivery to the cover region.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The review works out for Pakistan and the third one falls down for the hosts. Also the big wicket of the skipper, Mominul Haque. Khan floats this one up, lands it fuller around off, Haque presses forward and looks to defend but the ball spins away very nicely and whistles past the outside edge of Haque to Rizwan, who collects this, and the Pakistan contingent are up in celebration. Wait a minute, the umpire is unmoved right now. He does not think there was any bat on this. Babar Azam goes for the review straightaway and as soon as you see the replays, you know why they were so confident. A clear spike on UltraEdge and the on-field decision has been overturned.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Sajid Khan

Commentary: Tossed up, on middle, gently eased to the right of mid on for a quick single.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on off, defended out.
Strayed on the pads now, easily clipped through square leg for one.
Flatter around off, Rahim blocks it out. A great over by Sajid!
On middle, NHS keeps it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Seems like 14 is the cursed number for the Bangladeshi batters as this is the third batter who loses his wicket on the score of 14. Pakistan are well on top in this session and they have already snared 4 wickets so far. Faheem Ashraf hurls across a slightly shortish delivery, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto stands tall and slaps this one towards the point fielder. Sajid Khan dives ahead and takes this one. The Pakistanis are celebrating but the umpires converge and just want to ensure that this catch is a clean one and so, they ask the TV umpire for guidance, with their soft signal being out. Replays suggest that Khan's fingers were underneath the ball when he took the catch and hence, out is the decision.
Howout: c Sajid Khan b Faheem Ashraf

Commentary: Fuller outside off, left alone.
Angled into the off and middle pole, knocked to the leg side.
Bowled in the area of uncertainty and Das has no issues in leaving this alone.
Das gets off the mark! On middle and leg, clipped behind square leg for three runs.
Floated, around off, kept out.
Slightly shorter and outside off, dabbed towards point by Das.
Flatter this time, outside off and spins in slightly, kept out by Liton.
Now, Liton Das goes on the back foot and smothers the ball out on the deck.
On middle, the ball spins in, Das moves inside the line and Mohammad Rizwan dives to his left and stops the ball.
FOUR! The timing on this shot was sublime. Very full this time, around off, Liton Das gets underneath this and thumps this one through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, an easy leave for Rahim.
On a length on middle, worked off the pads through mid-wicket. Two taken before the fielder can cut it off.
Around off, pushed to covers.
On a length outside off, Rahim has no interest in playing at this.
Good-length around off, Rahim defends.
On middle, worked behind square on the leg side for a single to end the over.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahim presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Tosses it up, on middle. Rahim watchfully blocks it out.
Outside off, no turn at all. Rahim leaves it untouched.
On middle, Rahim nudges it to mid-wicket.
Sliding in on middle and leg. Rahim rocks back and plays this to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, outside off. Rahim drives it to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Poor line from Shaheen Afridi! Bowls it down the leg side, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to tuck but misses. The ball brushes off his thigh pad and races away to the fine leg fence.
Back of a length, on off. Rahim stays on the back foot and defends.
Back of a length again, on off. Rahim drops this down with soft hands.
Back of a length, on off. Rahim defends this down to the pitch.
On off, Rahim knocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Rahim defends it on the off side.
Floats it up, on middle. Das stays solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das pushes it on the off side off the back foot.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
Full and on middle, Das presses forward and blocks it out.
Angling in on leg, Das defends it out.
Full and on middle, driven towards covers. A maiden!
Short of a length on leg, Rahim looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad to short fine leg. The batters take a leg bye.
Back of a length, around off, nipping away. Liton Das looks to defend but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Short ball, on middle. Das ducks under it.
Short again, on middle. Das sits under it and evades it comfortably.
Short of a length, angling away, on off. Das sways away from the line and leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, on off. Das taps it towards covers.
Tosses it up, outside off. An easy leave for Rahim.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahim presses forward and blocks.
Just short! Loopy ball, on off. Rahim looks to defend but the ball takes off the outside edge. Played it with soft hands and thus, the ball does not carry to the first slip fielder.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up, on off. Rahim defends it watchfully.
Flatter ball, on middle. Rahim stays back and defends it out. Another maiden for Nauman Ali!
On a length, on middle. Das covers the line and presses this to mid off.
Back of a length, on off. Das hops and taps it to point for a quick single.
Short ball, on middle. Rahim ducks under it.
Short of a length, on middle. Rahim defends it down onto the pitch.
Full and outside off, Rahim shoulders arms to that.

Short of a length, on off. Rahim ducks too early on that occasion and Shaheen Afridi has a wry smile about this. He is continuing with his back-of-a-length delivery which indicates he wants another wicket here.
Short and outside off, Das camps back and cuts it through cover-point. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to a couple.
On off, pushed to covers.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das stays on the back foot and defends it watchfully.
Loopy ball, outside off. Das leaves it alone.
Full and outside off, turning away. Das lets it be.
Length ball, on middle. Rahim drops this one on the leg side.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahim works it towards covers.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball this time from Hasan Ali, on off. Rahim ducks underneath easily.
Length ball, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, Rahim prods and defends it towards point. A maiden!
Outside off, turning away. Das lets this one go. Sharp turn on that occasion.
Loopy ball, on off. Das presses forward and defends it solidly off the front foot.
On the pads, nudged to square leg for a single.
Floats it up, on middle. Rahim blocks it out.
Full and on leg, Rahim watchfully defends it on the leg side.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Rahim nudges it to mid on. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Goes full, on off. Das blocks it from the crease.
Length ball, on off. Das covers the line and defends it out on the off side.
On a good length, around off. Das blocks it towards covers with a straight bat.
Length ball, on middle. Das nudges it to mid on.
FOUR! That's a lovely shot! Fuller in length, outside off. Liton Das sees the width and leans onto it. He drives it elegantly through covers. Two fielders give it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Outside off, Das is not troubled by that line. He shoulders arms.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahim presses forward and blocks.
Tosses it up, on middle. Watchfully defended off the front foot.
Floats it up, on off. Rahim stays solid in his defence.
On off, blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Rahim goes back and cuts it towards covers.
On the pads, Rahim defends it on the leg side.
Length ball, on middle. Das tucks it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Similar line and length, Das nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off. Das shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, on off. Das looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
Play and a miss! Good-length ball, in the fourth stump channel, nipping away. Liton Das wants a feel of it. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through into the keeper's mitts.
Length ball, outside off. Das pushes it towards covers.
Loopy ball, on middle. Rahim hangs back and blocks it down onto the pitch.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Slower through the air, on middle. Swept away by Rahim to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Nicely played! Nauman Ali pulls his length back, outside off. Liton Das rocks back and cuts it very late to deep backward point for a boundary. The placement was excellent.
Flighted ball, on off. Das defends it on the off side.
On middle, defended watchfully.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rahim lets it sail through.
On a length, around off. Rahim taps it to point.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Width on offer, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim rides on the bounce and slaps it through cover-point to fetch himself a boundary. His first boundary after facing 52 balls. This shows the kind of temperament he persists.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Streaky this time! Length ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim presses forward and looks to push it to the off side. The ball goes off the outer half of the bat through gully for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Rahim leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, outside off, turning away. Liton Das looks to defend but gets beaten.
Loopy ball, on off, didn't spin at all. Das looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past first slip for a run.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Drifting it on leg, Rahim tucks it to short fine leg for a single.
On middle, Das stays solid in his defence.
Fuller in length, on middle. Rahim pushes it to mid on.
Full again, on off. Rahim knocks it back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Rahim drives it but finds the cover fielder.
On a length, on middle. Rahim works it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, well outside off. Rahim ignores it.
Fuller in length, on off. Rahim covers the sticks and pats it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Flatter this time from Nauman Ali, he bowls it outside off, Liton Das shuffles and cuts this one late through backward point. Fawad Alam chases after this but is no match as the ball finds the ropes.
Same line and length as the last ball, Das looks to late cut again but misses.
Outside off, LD shoulders arms.
Tossed up, around off, defended back onto the deck.
Flatter, around off, Das goes back and blocks it out.
Flighted around off, Liton gets ahead and pushes the ball away to the off side.
Shaheen starts this spell with a shortish delivery, outside off, this is cut away to the point fielder.
Outside off, on a length, Rahim leaves it alone.
Angled into the middle pole, pushed away to the on side by Rahim.
This is pitched up, around off, MR whips this straight to mid-wicket.
Shaheen Afridi changes things up and bowls a bouncer on middle, ducked under safely by Mushfiqur.
Slower in pace, fuller around off, Rahim eases this but finds the mid on fielder.
Ali floats this one up, full on off, nicely kept out.
Angled into the middle pole now, still Das shows the full face of the blade and blocks.
Loopy, around off, pushed away to the point region.
On the pads, flicked to the leg side for a run.
Too full, but on the pads this time, swept away by Rahim to the fielder at deep square leg for one.
Again, Ali strays and serves one on the pads, which Mushfiqur Rahim finds easy to whip away through mid-wicket. Two runs.
Short of a length, on middle and leg, Rahim looks to whip it across the line but misses and gets hit on the pad. A half-hearted appeal from Afridi but this looked to be too high.
Way outside off, no shot offered.
Full toss around off, hit to the cover fielder.

FOUR! The change of angle does not work and the 50-run stand has been brought up between these two. Shaheen comes around the wicket and bowls a loosener. Short and wide outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim waits, and then dabs it behind point. Boundary.
On off, blocked.
Full, on off, Rahim inside-edges this back onto his pad.
Turn on this! Fuller, looped up, outside off, Liton Das lunges ahead but the ball spins away and evades his outside edge.
On middle, defended.
Liton Das eases this fuller ball down to mid off. The batters scamper through for the run. The fielder does hit the stumps at the non-striker's end but Das was well in.
Darted on middle, blocked.
Nauman Ali goes fuller around off and middle, Mushfiqur Rahim gets low and slog-sweeps this to the left of the deep square leg fielder, who collects this one the bounce. Two runs taken.

Poor delivery. Fuller and sliding down the leg side, Mushfiqur Rahim easily gets low and sweeps this through short fine leg. By the time deep square leg can run to his right and collect and throw the ball, three runs are completed.
Around off, pushed to mid off.
On middle, played down to mid on now.
Fuller, outside off, left alone.
Drags his length way back now, this is almost a bouncer, around off, nicely swayed away from by Rahim.
FOUR! The boundaries are flowing along nicely now. On a length, around off, Mushfiqur Rahim leans into the drive and just smothers this through mid off. No point chasing after this.
On off and middle, blocked to the leg side.
Floated, around off, lands and turns in, Das goes back and defends to the leg side.
Around off, defended.
Short, on middle, nudged to square leg for one.
On middle and leg, blocked out gently.
Flighted around off, worked to mid on for a quick single.
Liton Das goes back and nicely nurdles this behind square on the leg side for a single.
Slightly behind the good length, on off and middle, blocked down on the pitch by Das.
Full on middle, played to mid on.
Around off, defended to the off side.
Afridi comes 'round the wicket and bowls a short ball around off, Liton taps this one towards square leg and changes ends.
Now, Afridi hurls across a yorker, around off. Rahim gets his bat down in time and blocks.

FOUR! Shot of the session so far. Rahim is playing a sublime knock here. Around off, on a drivable length, Mushfiqur Rahim shows the full face of the blade and gently pushes this one through mid on. Just a push but the timing on this means it will run away to the ropes.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Tossed up, on off. Das works it to mid-wicket. He wanted a single but is sent back by Rahim.
On off, worked to mid-wicket off the inner half for a single.
Flighted ball, on middle. Rahim steps out and pushes it to mid on.
Flatter ball, on off, Rahim makes room and looks to cut and does well to jam it to point.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Mushfiqur Rahim uses his feet and takes the ball on full. He smashes it towards long on for a boundary.
Fraction short, outside off. Das makes room and cuts it to cover-point.
Tosses it up, outside off. Das blocks it out.
Slower through the air, around off, pushed to point.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Liton Das has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller, around off, blocked out by Liton.
Full and on off, pushed to wide of mid on for a single. The fielder does well to stop that despite a little bit of fumble.
On the pads, tucked on the leg side.
SIX! BANG! The crowd erupts! Loopy ball, on middle. Liton Das advances down the track, makes perfect contact and sends the ball sailing over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. He moves onto 40 now.
Floats it up, on middle. Liton Das clips it on the leg side for a single.
Outside off, cut away to covers.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Rahim cuts it to point.
FOUR! Liton Das is on a roll! He is really looking in fine touch. Loopy ball, around off. Liton Das rocks back and cuts it through point for a boundary. The confidence is oozing out of his bat.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Full again, on off. Das defends it out.
Tosses it up, on middle. Das prods and watchfully blocks it out.
On off, kept out by Das.
Outside off, Das leaves it alone.

CATCH IT! That was the call from the Pakistani fielders. Sajid Khan bowls a loopy ball, turning in. Mushfiqur Rahim on the back foot clips it past short leg fielder for a single. Pakistan will feel they have missed out on a chance. Was a tough chance though!
Tossed up, on off. Das blocks it out.
Slower and drifting down leg, Das lets it go.
Pushed through on off, Das uses his feet and eases it past the bowler for one.
On off, Rahim blocks it out.
On leg, Rahim pads it away.
Flighted on off, Das prods across and then defends.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR LITON DAS! It has come at the right time for Bangladesh. His 10th half century in Tests.  Nauman Ali drops it short, outside off. Liton Das waits for it and then chops it to deep backward point to collect a boundary.
Tossed it up, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Very full, on off, patted back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das blocks it out.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on for a single.
OH! That was close! Floated delivery, on off, spinning back in sharply. Das stays back and looks to cut but gets an inside edge onto the pads. He needs to be careful here.
On off, worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on leg. Das clips it to deep square leg for a brace.
Slower through the air, on middle. Das presses forward and defends.
Drifting onto the pads, Das tucks it to backward square leg.
Loopy ball, outside off. Rahim lets it be.
Full and on off, driven to mid off for a quick single.
On off, pushed back to the bowler off the back foot.
Flighted, full and on middle. Das blocks it watchfully.
FOUR! Slower through the air, on off. Liton Das gets underneath the ball and drives it through covers. The ball races away to the boundary. 100-run partnership comes up as well between these two.
On off, blocked out.
On off, Rahim prods and whips it to mid on for a run.
On the pads, Das tucks it on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on off, Das comfortably defends it out.
On middle, turning in. Das nudges it on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on leg. Das looks to tuck but gets hit on the pads.
On off, Das defends it out off the front foot. Just a single from the over.
Good-length ball on off, defended out.
Short of a length, around off, Rahim blocks it out.
Fuller, way outside off, Rahim shoulders arms.
FOUR! Hasan Ali goes short this time and serves it just outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim goes back and with an angled bat, guides this one past the gully fielder. Boundary.

FOUR! Fifty for Mushfiqur Rahim! Wow, what a knock it has been from Mushfiqur Rahim. Bangladesh were having a tough time but he has steadied things wonderfully for them. Ali does not learn again, serves it short and wide, slapped behind point by Rahim for back-to-back boundaries.
On off, blocked.
Floated, around off, nudged to the leg side.
On middle, worked through mid-wicket for one.

Huge shout for lbw but not given! Tossed up, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim uses his feet and was looking to flick on the leg side. He misses out and gets hit on the pads. Sajid Khan appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. The ball goes off the pads to cover and the batters take a leg bye.
Khan dishes a flatter ball, around off and middle, Liton Das camps back and bangs this one through mid-wicket. They take the second before the ball is thrown back into the middle.
Flatter, outside off, punched through covers for one.
Another run as this is milked through mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Since this was bowled outside the off pole, Mushfiqur Rahim is not interested in playing at that.
Mushfiqur Rahim flicks this through square leg and rotates the strike.
On off, worked through covers for one.
Good-length ball outside off, Rahim steps ahead but decides to leave it.
Short and in the line of the stumps, Rahim sits under this one and lets it go.
Floated, lands outside off but turns back in, this is nudged to the leg side.
Straight to the short leg fielder! Dropped short again, on middle, Liton Das goes back and thumps this straight to Abid Ali at short leg, who blocks it with his leg.
On middle, tucked to the on side.
Outside off, pushed away to point.
Flatter, around off, nudged just ahead of the short leg fielder.
Short, on off, Das steps out and flicks this to the short leg fielder on the bounce. He makes his way back in before the fielder can throw to ball to Rizwan, who whips the bails off.
Back of a length, on off, blocked.
Rahim plays this towards mid-wicket but for no runs.

Smart cricket. Short and wide outside off, Rahim chops this one to the slip cordon, where Mohammad Rizwan collects and throws it to the wickets at the striker's end and hits too. Rahim was going nowhere and he notices Liton Das coming across for a run and they complete it with ease.
Full toss outside off, Das looks to push but misses.
Outside off, fuller in length, driven but straight to the cover fielder.
Liton Das has just blocked that from his crease.
Full on middle, played through mid on for one.
Tossed up, on off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle, gently dabbed to short leg.
Darted on middle, hit across towards mid-wicket for a run.
On middle, worked to square leg.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On a length, around off, nipping in, Das keeps it out.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Fullish this time, on the middle pole, blocked towards mid on.
Pitched up, around off, slightly slower in pace, Liton dabs it down.
Yorker on middle and off, Liton gets his bat across and blocks well.
Around off, on a length, pushed back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Drops it short, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On the pads, Das tucks it to short leg.
Loopy ball, on middle, Das blocks it out.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, on middle. Das stays solid in his defence.
On middle, blocked out by Das.
On a length, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim covers the line and tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Das digs it out to point.
On a length, on off. Das plays it towards covers.
On middle, angling in. Das nudges it to mid on.
Short but not too short, on middle. Das sways away and ducks under it.
Fuller in length, outside off. Das drives it to cover.
Floats it up, on middle. Rahim prods and knocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, tucked on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Rahim clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Das uses his feet and drills it down to long on for one.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim waits for the ball to come, leans onto it and steers it through covers for a boundary.
Full and around off, bunted down to long on for a single. 7 runs from the over.
Short of a length, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim pulls it over short leg. Didn't quite get the hold of it but still gets a single.
Short of a length, outside off. Liton Das rides on the bounce and punches it through covers off the back foot. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Back of a length, outside off. Rahim taps it to point.
Short ball, on middle. Rahim sits under it.
Short again, going down leg. Mushfiqur Rahim raises his blade to shouder arms.
Short again, ducked under again. No harm done!
In the air, but safe! Loopy ball, on middle. Liton Das looks to tuck but gets a leading edge. The ball lobs towards short extra cover and lands safe.
On middle, tucked on the leg side off the inside edge. The ball lands well wide of short leg.
Tosses it up, full and on off. Das defends it out.
Flighted delivery, Liton Das eases it down to long on for one.
Outside off, blocked out.
Tosses it up, on off. Rahim punches it through covers for one.
Shaheen Afridi continues with his short-length delvieries. Bowls this one short, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim gets his head out of the way and evades it comfortably.
On a length, on off. Rahim taps it to point for a single.

DROPPED! Can you believe it? The short length finally worked but the catch is dropped. Short ball, on middle. Liton Das pulls it towards mid-wicket. Sajid Khan there couldn't hold onto it and puts down a sitter. A straightforward chance goes begging. How costly will this prove for Pakistan? Shaheen Afridi cannot believe what he just saw and is in total distraught.
Short of a length agian, Das turns this to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Rahim ducks under this short ball.
Short again, Rahim swivels and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tosses it up, on off. Rahim blocks it out.
Drifting down leg, Rahim defends it watchfully.
On the pads, tickled to fine leg for a run.
Loopy ball, on off. Das stays deep and dabs it to short leg.
Tosses it up, on off. Das defends it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, on off. Das whips this one through short leg fielder's legs for a single.
WIDE! Short ball, on middle. Liton Das leaves it alone. Well above Das' head and the umpire signals it as wide.
Short of a length, outside off. Das dabs this one through point for a single.
Length ball, going down leg. Left alone. Mohammad Rizwan does well to moves to his left and collect the ball.
On a length, outside off. Rahim lets it be.
Slower ball, on the pads. Rahim clips it on the leg side and gets to the other end.
FOUR! Delightful batting! Touch fuller, outside off. Liton Das uses the pace of the ball and guides it towards deep backward point for a boundary.
Fuller in length, on middle. Das flicks it to deep square leg for a single. 150 partnership comes up between these two as well.
Tossed up, on middle, Das works this square on the on side and rotates the strike. 200 comes up for Bangladesh!
On middle, defended to the short leg fielder.
Flighted around off, gently pushed away to covers.
Fuller on middle, defended again.
Tossed up right now, outside off, MR pushes this back onto the deck.
Mushfiqur Rahim plays this to the cover region.
Back of a length, around off, coming in, Liton dabs it down on the leg side.

Well fielded by Nauman Ali in the deep! This is bowled on the shorter trajectory, way outside the off stump, Liton Das slaps this to deep point. Ali runs to his right, dives, and stops the ball. Two taken.
Around off, pushed to covers now.
FOUR! Well played! Short ball again, outside off, the ball does not bounce too much and Liton Das slaps this one over mid-wicket. A couple of bounces and it goes past the ropes.
A single as this is played through point.
Good-length ball on off, hit back to the bowler.

Drops short! Floated, around off, Liton Das looks to push this to the off side but the ball spins away and kisses the outside edge. The ball goes towards Babar Azam at first slip but it drops just ahead of him.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Full, outside off, blocked.
Given more flight, but on middle, Das presses ahead and dabs this back on the deck.
Short now, outside off, cut away to point.
Flatter again, outside off, slapped to covers for one.
Short, outside off, turns in, Das goes back and pushes it to Sajid.
Same length, on middle and leg now, LD works this to square leg.
Very full, on off, Das gets his bat ahead and defends.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
A carbon copy of the previous delivery.
Liton Das sees that the length is shortened and skips out of the track but only manages to push it back to the bowler.
Floated, around off, pushed back to Ali.

NO BALL! Floated again, fuller around off and middle, Mushfiqur Rahim gets low and looks to sweep but seems to have hit it along the ground to short leg, where the ball deflects via his body, to the mid-wicket fielder, who takes it. An appeal is made but the umpire says no. Both the umpires converge and take this upstairs with their soft signal being not out, but Nauman Ali's foot was not behind the crease and hence, will be a no ball and not out too.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
On middle, blocked.
Darted on middle and leg, flicked behind square leg for one.
Full, outside off, pushed to point.
Full, outside off, jammed through covers for one.
On middle, played to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Sajid serves this short and on middle and going down leg with the angle, Liton Das backs away and pumps this one through square leg. Not a good delivery from Khan and he gets punished.
Outside off, dabbed behind point and the batters are able to come back for three. Das is into the 90s now!
Fullish, outside off, Rahim backs away and punches this through cover-point. They run well and come back for the second run too.
Full, on off, jammed out to covers.
Angles a fuller ball outside off, Rahim jams it out to covers again.
Tossed up on off, pushed to covers.
Flatter, way outside off, a late dab from Das this time towards short third man. Alam chases and stops it but not before the lads out in the middle run two runs.
Strays on the pads, nudged through square leg for one.
Two leg byes! On the pads, Rahim misses his tuck but the ball deflects via his pad to the fine leg region for a couple of leg byes.
Mushfiqur Rahim has just watchfully blocked this out.
Mushfiqur Rahim will keep the strike as he works this behind square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim swivels and looks to smash it on the leg side but miscues. The ball goes off the pad to fine leg for a single. The umpire gives it runs off bat though.
Slower ball, on leg. Das nudges it on the leg side for a single.
On off, blocked out.
Tosses it up, on off. Rahim looks to cut but chops it back to the keeper.
On middle, turned to the leg side.
Loopy ball, wide of off. Rahim drives it to mid off.
Loopy ball, on off. Das blocks it from the crease.
Floats it up, on leg. Das defends it out.
Tossed up, on off. Das does well to block it out.
On off, turning away. Das negotiates with it well and fends it to the off side.
This is nudged to mid on. Liton Das is looking anxious to score those 4 important runs to get to his personal milestone.
Outside off, dabbed to point. A maiden!
Tad short, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
On the pads, turned to square leg for a single. 3 runs short of a century now.
Full and on off, well struck by Rahim to mid off for a single.
Tosses it up, on middle. Das is not in a hurry to bring his century as he blocks this one out.
On middle, driven back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Das steps out and pushes it to mid on for a single. He keeps the strike.
Slower through the air, on leg. Liton Das pushes it to mid on for a single. He moves onto 99!
On middle, swept to deep square leg for a single. That will bring Liton Das back to strike.

THERE IT IS! MAIDEN CENTURY FOR LITON DAS! Full and on off, Liton Das prods and pushes it to mid off for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Liton Das gets to his maiden Test century and the crowd are going bonkers. He raises his bat pointing towards the sky. This has been a knock of the highest quality. A loud round of applause from the dressing room as well. Could have been out if the ball had hit the stumps.
Slower on leg, turned on the leg side.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Rahim blocks it out.
Very full, outside off. Rahim drives it straight to mid off.
Flighted ball, on leg. Das defends it well.
Loopy ball, on leg. Das defends it back to the bowler.
Fraction short and on middle. Das clips it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, outside off. Das went hard on the drive, places it through covers. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Drifting down leg, Rahim lets it go.
Flatter ball, on off. Rahim tucks it on the leg side.
Tosses it up, outside off. Das defends it on the off side.
Full and on middle, Das stays solid in his defence.
Floats it up, on middle. Das blocks it out.
Outside off, Das makes room and cuts it through cover-point for a single.
Loopy ball, full and on middle. Rahim presses forward and blocks.
On off, Rahim taps it to covers.
Length ball, down leg. Das looks to flick but misses.
Length ball again, on leg. Das works it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, on leg, nipping back in. Liton Das jams it out to mid on.
Similar delivery, on leg. Liton Das flicks it this time to deep square leg for one.
Length ball, going down leg. Rahim lets it be. Shaheen Afridi is finding it difficult to control his length with the new cherry.
FOUR! MORE RUNS! Length ball, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim tickles it down to fine leg for a boundary.
On a length, outside the off pole, no problem for Liton Das as he makes a leave.
Around off, on a length, Liton Das looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes through short third man for a single.
Around off, blocked to the off side.
Fuller in length, outside off, shaping away, well left by Rahim.
Angled into the off and middle pole, Rahim nudges this to mid-wicket.
On middle, flicked to square leg.
Good-length ball, outside off, Das looks to drive but gets an inside edge, which sends the ball rolling to deep square leg, for one.
Slightly behind the good length, on off, blocked to covers.
Around off, defended towards gully.
A carbon copy of the previous ball. Defended out by Rahim.
Sliding down the leg side this time, Rahim misses his tuck.
Served on a length outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim is not interested in playing at that.
On off, kept out.
Around off, length, pushed to point.
Shaping away from a length outside off, Das just shoulders arms.
Same line and length as the previous ball, left alone again.
Another leave from Liton as this was again bowled wider outside the off pole.
Four leaves in a row! Outside off, not played at.
Short of a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim dabs it through gully for a single. 200 partnership comes up between these two now!
Lazy looking shot that from Das! Length ball, on off, nipping away. Liton Das has a poke at it but gets beaten onthe outside edge.
Looks like the body is taking a pouding! That was short and way down the leg side. Das leaves it alone. Mohammad Rizwan dives to his left to pouch it.
Full and angling across, outside off. Liton Das presses forward and tries to drive but misses. The ball stays a litle low and rolls to the keeper.

FOUR! This is brilliant from Das! Overpitched delivery from 'round the wicket, outside off. Liton Das drives that one through covers for a boundary. He looks completely drained after playing that shot.
Full and on the stumps, Das turns that one away to mid-wicket.
Starts with short and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim rocks back and cuts it towards covers. The fielder there dives to his right and stops the ball. A single is taken.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das is solid in his defence.
Shortish, outside off. Das punches it towards covers off the back foot for a single.
Flighted delivery, on off. Rahim strides forward to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to backward point.
Angling in with the arm, on middle and leg. Rahim flicks it to short fine leg.
Tossed up, very full, on middle and leg. Rahim drives it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Das shoulder arms to that one.
Goes a touch fuller and wider, outside off. Das leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off. Das keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it down the pitch.
On a good length, outside off, little bit of width on offer. Das strides forward and drives but finds the cover fielder.
Little bit of movement there but not close enough to interest the batsman. On a good length, outside off. Das ignores that easily.

OUT! LBW! Good-length ball, on middle, shaping in sharply. Das looks to defend but misses. He gets rapped on the back pad. Hasan Ali appeals for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Hasan Ali convinces Babar Azam to go for a review. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows three reds. Only height could have saved him but the Ball Tracker shows wickets hitting and Pakistan are delighted. The on-field call is overturned. They have got the prized wicket of Liton Das who was well set. Brilliant review from Pakistan and they will now look to build on this. Liton Das has to walk back to the pavilion after a magnificent knock.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bad line from Shaheen Afridi! Onto the pads, Mushfiqur Rahim misses his flick. The ball brushes off the pads and dribbles away to the fine leg fence.
Short of a length, on leg. Rahim blocks that one from the crease.
Back of a length, on middle, some hint of away movement. Rahim defends it with soft hands.
On a length, on middle. Rahim gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Fuller in length, on off. Rahim presses forward and defends it with dead bat to point.
Back of a length, on off. Rahim stays on the back foot and defends it to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Yasir Ali lets it be.
On a good length, on off, angling in. Yasir Ali covers the sticks and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on middle. Yasir Ali is firm in his defence. Blocks it with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Short ball from Hasan Ali this time, on middle, nipping in. Yasir Ali ducks underneath.
Length ball, in the trajectory of uncertainty, shaping away. Yasir Ali shoulders arms to that.
Good-length ball, on off. Yasir Ali punches it off the back foot towards extra cover. A maiden from Hasan Ali!
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it for the keeper to collect.
This time, it's on a length, on leg. Rahim stands on his toes and clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Yasir Ali sways away from the line and sits under it.
On a good length, outside off, angling away. Yasir Ali dabs it to point.
Much straighter this time, on top of off. Yasir Ali blocks it towards covers.
Length ball, down leg. Yasir Ali looks to flick but misses. Mohammad Rizwan dives across to collect the ball.
Length ball, on off. Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. An easy leave for Rahim as he shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, on off, shaping away. Mushfiqur Rahim is solid in his defence.
On a length, in the fourth stump channel. Mushfiqur Rahim pokes it towards backward point for a single.
In-slanter, down leg. Yasir Ali misses his flick. The ball goes off the pads into the keeper's mitts.

NOT OUT! Yasir Ali survives! Good-length ball, angling in, on leg. Yasir Ali looks to defend but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Big appeal from Hasan Ali and Co. for an lbw but is turned down by the umpire. Babar Azam signals 'T' at the last second. It's a fair delivery. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing as it is going down the leg side. Pakistan burn a review.
Angled on the pads, nudged to the leg side for a run.
A bouncer around off, Yasir Ali sways back on this occasion.
FOUR! That is quite a way to get your Test career underway. Pitched up, wider outside off, Yasir Ali presses forward and punches this with authority through cover-point. No stopping that.
Dragged short and outside off, left alone easily.
Outside off again, shorter, no shot offered by Ali.
Fuller outside off, left alone.
On a length, on leg. Rahim clips it to deep square leg. He crosses ends.
Full and on middle, Yasir Ali blocks it out.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP!  Hasan Ali is making the ball talk. Good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Right through the defence as Yasir Ali presses forward to drive but misses. The ball goes through the gap between bat and pad and crashes the stumps behind him. Always a beautiful sight for the bowler. Hasan Ali has been very productive so far and celebrates it with his trademark celebration. He bags his third wicket and sends Yasir Ali back walking. Not a fruitful debut for him.
Oh! Full-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Mehidy Hasan is stuck at his crease as he look to have a poke at it. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
BEATEN AGAIN! Full and around off, nipping away. Mehidy Hasan is stuck at his crease again as he tries to flirt with the ball. He is fortunate to not get an outside edge there.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it untouched.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Shaheen Afridi comes 'round the wicket and angles a length ball, around off, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to tuck this away to the leg side but the outside edge is induced and the ball runs away through point for a boundary.
Outside off, dabbed to point now.
Fuller outside off, easily left alone.
Around off, pushed back on the deck.
Outside off, on a length, driven but straight to the point fielder.
Fullish now, outside off, the ball stays a touch low and Hasan looks to push it, but the ball sneaks underneath his blade to the keeper.
Outside off, no shot offered.
Shortish, down the leg side, Hasan gets inside the line and leaves.
Good-length ball on off, defended out.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Hasan ducks down and watches it sail over him.
Mehidy gets underway! Around off, on a length, a solid looking punch through covers. The man in the ring half-stops it and by the time he can collect the ball again, two are taken.
Left alone as this was bowled outside off.
On off, blocked.
Digs in a short ball around off, Rahim moves away from the line of the ball.
Short again, outside off though, dabbed down to gully.
On off, pushed away to covers.
Fullish on off again, Rahim blocks it out.
Around off, in the slot too, nicely driven through point by Mehidy Hasan and the batters collect a couple.
This is solidly defended out by Mehidy.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
This is served outside off, on a length, MH pushes it away to the off side.
Fuller, outside off, Mehidy Hasan looks to defend but the ball stays a touch low and beats his outside edge.
On off, played towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Slants across a fuller ball, outside off, Hasan does not fiddle with it.
Around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave.
Fuller, around off, Hasan pushes this to the mid off region.
Again, in the zone of uncertainty, outside off, Hasan looks to have a poke at this but the ball whistles past his blade to the keeper.
Good-length on off, blocked to point.
Faheem Ashraf starts his spell with a length ball outside off, Rahim watches it sail past him to the keeper.
Slipped down the leg side, Rahim misses his tuck here.
Faheem Ashraf again sprays this one down the leg side, the tuck is missed yet again.
On off, good length, punched down to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mushfiqur Rahim has to go back for 91 and the review does not save him. Ashraf serves this on a length, in the fourth stump channel, Rahim looks to defend this close to his body, but it seems like he has nicked this, as the ball goes to Rizwan, who collects and appeals and the finger goes up. Rahim goes for the review straightaway, but there was a loud sound as the ball passed the bat, so it is surprising that he has taken this. UltraEdge rolls in and there is a clear spike as the ball passes the bat. At the same time though, the lower part of Mushfiqur Rahim's bat also looks to be brushing his pad. The umpire sticks with his original decision but Rahim feels as though the noise was off his bat touching his pad. Nevertheless, he has to go back and his brilliant knock comes to an end.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Faheem Ashraf

Commentary: Fuller, outside off, Taijul Islam leans ahead and pushes this to point for one.
Loopy ball, on leg. Taijul Islam defends it on the leg side.
Full and on leg, Taijul Islam blocks it from the crease.
Tosses it up, on off. Taijul Islam prods to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to backward point.
On middle, kept out.
Onto the pads, Taijul Islam turns this to short fine leg.
Floats it up, on leg. Taijul Islam defends it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Mehidy Hasan knocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, on off. Mehidy Hasan drives it to mid off.
Full and on middle. Hasan drives it off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler.
Length ball, on middle, tucked on the leg side.

FOUR! Lucky runs! Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan looks to punch it to the off side. The ball goes off the inside edge towards fine leg. The fielder from deep square leg tries to stop the ball but fails to do so. A boundary.
FOUR! Much better from Mehidy Hasan! Length ball, outside off. Mehidy Hasan drives it towards deep covers for a boundary.
Full, on middle. Taijul Islam eases it back to the bowler.
A full toss, on middle. Taijul Islam defends it out.
Onto the pads, Taijul Islam clips it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball, on leg. Taijul Islam blocks it out.
Tosses it up, around off. Taijul Islam lunges forward to push it back to the bowler.
Edged but safe! Tosses it up, around off. Taijul Islam looks to defend but misses. The ball goes off the outside edge through keeper and first slip towards third man. Three runs taken.
Outside off, Taijul Islam steers this behind point for one.
Very full, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it on the off side.
FOUR! These are handy runs for Bangladesh! Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan rides on the bounce and slices it over the slip cordon towards third man for a boundary.
On off, left alone.
Good-length ball, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball, going down leg. Mehidy Hasan looks to flick but misses.
Loopy ball, on off. Taijul Islam presses forward to defend.
Tosses it up, around off. Taijul Islam looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, blocked out.
Flighted ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on off, Taijul Islam is solid in his defence.
A maiden! Floats it up on off, Taijul Islam defends it off the front foot.
Good timing and good fielding! Fuller in length, on off. Mehidy Hasan drives it to cover. The fielder dives to his right to stop a certain boundary. Faheem Ashraf appreciates the fielder as well.
On a length, on leg. Mehidy Hasan tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Taijul Islam defends it towards covers.
Faheem Ashraf comes 'round the wicket, bowls it outside off. Taijul Islam defends it towards covers.
Short ball, on leg. Taijul Islam pulls it to deep square leg to collect a single.
Fuller in length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan clears his front leg and flicks it but straight to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, around off. Taijul Islam looks to defend but the ball goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket. The batters take a single.
Quicker, around off. Mehidy Hasan pats it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Some aggression from Mehidy Hasan! Loopy ball, on off. Mehidy Hasan advances down the track and heaves it towards long off for a boundary. 300 up for Bangladesh with that boundary!
On middle, blocked out.
Slower through the air, on middle. Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
Flighted ball, on middle. Mehidy Hasan comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler. Sajid Khan flings the ball back to Mohammad Rizwan. Little bit of frustration there from the bowler.
Very full, outside off. Taijul Islam knocks it towards covers.
Bangs in short, on off. Taijul Islam reads the length early and ducks under it with ease.
FOUR! Well played! These are precious runs for Bangladesh! Back of a length, outside off. Taijul Islam hops and guides it through covers with soft hands for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! A lot fuller and straigher this time, outside off. Taijul Islam looks to drive. This time, the ball kisses the outside edge and flies towards first slip where Abdullah Shafique takes a good catch diving to his right. That's smart bowling from Shaheen Afridi. A good change from Babar Azam as it pays dividend.
Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Length ball, going down leg. Left alone.
Fuller in length, on middle. Abu Jayed does well to dig it out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short and spinning down the leg side, Mehidy Hasan swivels and hooks this one to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Flighted, around off, kept out.
Tossed up, on off, pushed to the leg side.
On off and middle, nudged to the mid-wicket region.
Floated, on off, Hasan skips down and thumps this down to long on for a run.
A bumper on middle and leg, Mehidy Hasan sits under this one.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Short and on the body, Hasan deflects this past the keeper towards fine leg. Mohammad Rizwan gives it chase and throws the ball back into the middle. Two taken.
Short of a length, on off, Hasan defends it out.
FOUR! Well played. On a shortish length, around off, Mehidy Hasan pulls this one towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
A quicker short ball around off this time, Mehidy Hasan gets low and looks to power it to the leg side but misses.
Floated, on middle, knocked to the leg side.
Tosses it up, around off, kept out.
A solid front-foot defense from Jayed here.
Fuller, angling on middle and leg, Jayed misses his defense and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Very full on off, jammed out by Abu.

Two leg byes! Good work by Alam. Fuller, on the pads, Abu Jayed and Mohammad Rizwan both miss the ball and the ball runs away to the third man fence. Fawad Alam and Babar Azam give this a chase and Alam pushes the ball back in time.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Around middle and leg, Hasan looks to flick but misses.
Short, around off, Hasan defends this one out.
Bangs a short ball, on leg. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
On a length, on leg. Tucked on the leg side.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan dabs it towards gully.
FOUR! Nicely played! Too full and slower, outside off. Abu Jayed gets low, waits for the ball to come and smacks it past mid on for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Flighted, around off, Abu defends it out.
Outside off, Abu makes a leave.
Fuller on middle and leg, kept out.
Floated, on middle, Abu blocks well.
Short of a length, around off, dabbed to the leg side.
Outside off, on a length, pushed through point.
Around off and middle, tapped to the right of the mid on fielder.
Short and down the leg side, Hasan makes a leave.
FOUR! He has smashed that one! What a cracking shot! He hit that very hard. A touch short, outside off, Mehidy Hasan stands tall and hoicks this one over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Around off, on a length, nudged to the leg side for a quick single.
On middle and leg, kept out.
Floated, outside off, Hasan plays this through mid off for a run.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up, around off, the ball lands and spins away slightly as Jayed looks to defend but misses.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Nauman Ali serves this fuller, around off, Abu Jayed gets low and slog-sweeps this hard towards wide long on. There is a man in the deep but the ball runs away to the ropes.
Short, around off, kept out.
Short again, outside off, hooked over square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Hasan Ali takes another wicket and Pakistan need one more. Shortish this time, around off, Abu Jayed looks to defend but the extra bounce does him in. He hangs his bat in defense but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to Abdullah Shafique at first slip, who pouches this with ease.
Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Hasan Ali

Commentary: OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Hasan Ali grabs two-in-two and ends with a 5-fer! He has bowled supremely well today and he will be very happy to end Bangladesh's innings. Around off, on a length, the ball lands and shapes in slightly, Ebadot Hossain looks to defend but misses and the wickets behind take a beating. BANGLADESH END ON 330!
Abu Jayed starts with a length ball around middle and leg, Abid defends this one out.
This is pitched around off, on a length again, Abid defends it to the off side.
Around off, on a length, the ball seams away this time as Abid Ali looks to put bat on ball and misses.
FOUR! That is some way to get off the mark for Ali. A half-volley this time, around off, Abid Ali leans ahead and creams this one through covers. Boundary.
Pitched up, around off, AA pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off, pushed away to the cover region.
Fuller, around off, solidly kept out.
Slightly behind the good length, around off again, AS blocks with a straight bat.
Short and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique makes a leave.
Back of a length, outside off, dabbed away to the off side.
Around off, on a length, AS steps forward and defends it out.
Width on offer outside off, Abdullah Shafique chops this one straight to point. Ebadot Hossain begins with a maiden!
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
On middle, kept out.
Fullish on middle, pushed away towards mid on.
Short of a length, around off, Abid works this to mid on.
This is pitched up from Jayed, outside off, Abid Ali watches closely and makes a leave.
Around off, AA works this through mid on and scampers across for a single.
Abid Ali makes an easy leave as this was bowled outside the off pole.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Good-length on off, Ali defends this solidly towards covers.
On off, length, blocked.
Behind the good length area, outside off, jags back slightly, Abid defends this with an angled bat.
Quick, full, outside off, no shot offered.
Short of a length, around off, Abdullah Shafique punches this to the cover region.
Abdullah Shafique has just watchfully blocked this out.
Again, behind the good length region, outside off, AS shows the full face of the blade and keeps it out.
Abdullah Shafique scores his first runs in Test cricket! Shortish, width offered outside off, Abdullah Shafique punches this through point and collects a brace.
Short of a length, around off, Abdullah Shafique slams the door shut with a solid defense.
On middle, played down to mid on.
Outside off, on a length, Ali blocks it well.
A bouncer around off, angling in, Abid Ali moves away from the line of the delivery.
Another bouncer outside off, Abid Ali drops his gloves and lets it pass.
FOUR! A good shot. On a shortish length, outside the off pole, Abid Ali waits for it and then sweetly punches this through point and gets a boundary.
Around off, on a length, Abid Ali looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and whistles past the wickets to the keeper.
FOUR! Overpitched delivery, outside off, Abid Ali presses forward and crashes this one through point.
On off, defended.
FOUR! Another boundary and Pakistan have started really well. This is pitched up now, on off, Abdullah Shafique whips this one across the line and the ball speeds away through mid-wicket.
On a length, on off, pushed away to the off side.
Yorker, on off, jammed out to covers.
Closer to the off pole, on a length, easily fended out by Abdullah.
Outside off, back of a length, Abdullah Shafique taps this one towards point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Abid Ali lets it sail through.
Drags his length back, on off. Abid Ali pulls it through mid-wicket. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Length ball, in the channel outside off. Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms to that.
Good-length ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique stabs it to the off side.
Back of a length again, outside off. Abdullah Shafique punches it towards covers off the back foot.
Starts with a quicker delivery, full and on off. Abid Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Floats it up, around off. Abid Ali rocks back and cuts it through cover-point for a single.
Full, around off. Blocked out.
Given some flight, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Slower through the air, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to block.
Tosses it up, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it towards covers.
FOUR! Lucky boundary! Length ball, outside off. Abid Ali throws the kitchen sink at it. The ball didn't bounce that much and it takes the inside edge. It races past the keeper to the fine leg fence.
On a length, on off. Abid Ali punches it to extra cover.
Full, angling in on off. Abid Ali defends it down to the pitch.
Keeps it full, on off. Abid Ali drives but finds the cover fielder.
Back of a length, angling in, on off. Abid Ali looks to punch it on the up. The ball stays a little low and goes off the under edge to point.
On the pads, Abid Ali works it to backward square leg. He looks for two but bumps into Ebadot Hossain while turning for the second run. The bowler straightaway apologises. Only a single.
Tossed up, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Nicely tosses up, outside off, driven towards covers.
Very full, Abid Ali drives it to mid off.
Flatter delivery, on middle, tucked on the leg side.
Flatter delivery, coming in with the arm. Abid Ali misses his tuck and gets hit on the pads. Bangladesh appeal for an lbw but it's going down leg.
Outside off, driven to mid off.
Fuller in length, around off. Abdullah Shafique strides forward and blocks it with a dead bat.
On a good length, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the off side.
A touch fuller, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
On a good length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique works it towards covers.
Length ball, outside off, dabbed towards point.
Good-length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but misses. The ball goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique drives it nicely through covers. Mominul Haque gives it a chase and keeps it down to a couple.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards covers.
On off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle, patted back to the bowler.

Floated delivery, on off. Abdullah Shafique camps back and defends with his pad close to the bat. Taijul Islam pleads the umpire for an lbw but not given. They discuss about taking the review but does not go for it at the end. It looked like pad first though. With 3 reviews available, Bangladesh could have gone for it. Yup, Replay shows it was pad first and hawkeye shows three reds as well. Bangladesh misses out on an opportunity. They could have had their first wicket.
On middle, worked on the leg side.
SIX! BAM! Short of a length, on middle. Abid Ali sits back and sends the ball sailing over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Outside off, Abid Ali looks to cut but misses as the ball stays a little low.
On a length, on middle. Abid Ali knocks it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Abid Ali looks to punch it but miscues it off the inside part of the bat to mid on.
On a length on middle, Ali clips it to short mid-wicket.
Floated, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up, fuller on off, AS blocks well.
Dragged short this time, outside off, slapped through point for a run.
Flighted on off, AA blocks.
Islam goes very full, on off, Ali strides ahead and taps the ball on the deck.
Flighted, on off, pushed down to mid on.
Good-length delivery on off, Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Good running! On off, a bit of nip back, length, Abdullah Shafique hits this towards mid on and the batters sneak a run.
Fuller, around off, nudged through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Good-length delivery now, outside off, Abid Ali smothers the ball out and denies the single.
On a shorter trajectory now, outside off, pulled hard to the right of the mid-wicket fielder, who dives and stops this.
Abid Ali tucks this straight to the short mid-wicket fielder again.
Full on middle and leg, defended to the on side.
Floated, outside off, eased through covers for a single.
On middle, kept out.
Abid Ali has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short in length, around off, blocked.
On the pads, clipped to square leg. Abid Ali wants a run but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to Hasan.
Shorter, outside off, knocked through mid-wicket for one.
Floated, outside off, Abid gets ahead and gently defends it out.
Around off and middle, defended.
This is on middle and leg, easily blocked out.
Loopy, on off, Ali gets forward and defends. Just 1 off Mehidy's first over!
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
It is on middle, solidly blocked out.
Outside off, pushed away to covers.
Darted on middle and leg, kept out.
Given loop, around off, blocked.
Full on middle, the flick is connected towards square leg but it does not result in any runs.
Flatter, outside off, easily milked through mid on for a single.
Floated again, outside off, Abdullah Shafique now knocks this through mid on for a single.
The third time on the trot that the ball is pushed down towards long on for one.
Dragged short and on off, kept out.
Full on off, blocked.
Loopy around off, Abdullah Shafique works this to the man at mid on.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Abid Ali skips down the track to this shortish delivery and pushes it to covers.
On middle and leg now, pushed back to the bowler.
Quicker, fuller, on off, Abid Ali steps out and inside-edges the shot onto his pad. An appeal for LBW but turned down.
Quicker again, on off, blocked.
Given loop, around off, pushed to the leg side.

SIX! What a shot from the debutant! Mehidy Hasan serves this fuller, tossed up, around off, Abdullah Shafique skips out, gets to the pitch of the ball, and smacks this one over deep mid-wicket. 50 up for Pakistan and the 50-run stand between these two is also up!
Quicker and fuller on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and defends.
Flatter, on off, blocked to point now.
On the pads, nudged to the short leg fielder on the bounce.
Floated, on middle, flicked through square leg for one.
Gets his bat across and shuts the door with a solid looking defense.
Full on off, jammed out to the leg side.
Outside off, fuller again, stroked through covers for one.
Loopy, around off, Abid Ali works this one through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

FOUR! That was so well done by Ali. Another boundary. Taijul Islam serves this fuller and on middle and leg, Abid Ali gets low and just works this through short fine leg and the ball finds its way to the ropes.
Short, outside off, pumped to sweeper cover for a single.
Around off, a firm push to the cover region by Abid.
Around middle, Abid Ali cuts it off the back foot through covers for a couple of runs.
Loopy ball, on middle. Ali blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Abid Ali drives it through covers for a couple more.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full and wide, outside off. Abid Ali leans onto it and drives it through backward point. The ball races away to the boundary. Ali moves onto 47 now!
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, around off, tapped towards point.
Full and on off, pushed to mid on.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique shuffles and clips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, on off, Abdullah Shafique defends it out.
Full and on off, nudged to mid-wicket.
Floated ball, on middle, tucked behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full again, on off, driven to mid off.
Slanting in, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Loopy ball, on middle, Abdullah Shafique works it on the leg side.
On off, defended to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle, nudged to square leg.
Full and on middle, clipped to mid-wicket.
Sprays this one down leg, Abdullah Shafique gets low and looks to sweep but misses. Liton Das appeals for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
On a good length, on off. Abid Ali defends it from the crease.
Full and on middle, defended onto the pitch. Some sloppy fielding allows the batters to take a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique prods and knocks it to mid on.
Shortish, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it through covers for a brace.
Fuller in length, on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to mid on.
Full and on off, driven past the bowler to mid on.

Loopy ball, on middle, Abid Ali tucks it on the leg side. Total mix-up between the two batters there as Abid Ali first takes off for a single but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique. Then Abdullah Shafique calls for a single but Abid Ali says no. A misfield too and in the end, no harm done!
FIFTY! Loopy ball, on leg. Abid Ali turns it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs. He gets to his fifty and raises his bat to the dug out. His third Test fifty!
On middle, blocked out.
This is turned to mid-wicket with the spin for a run.
Very full, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it back to the bowler.
On off, Abdullah Shafique defends it with soft hands.
On a length, on off. Abid Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On middle, tucked to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. AS pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the leg side.
On a good length, but well outside off. Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Runs straightaway! Loopy ball, on middle. Abid Ali works it through mid-wicket. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Tossed up, on middle, punched off the back foot towards extra cover.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Floated ball, on middle, defended on the leg side.
Full and on leg, patted back to the bowler.
FOUR! Good confident-looking shot! Shortish, outside off. Abid Ali cuts it through backward point to fetch himself a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Ali tucks it on the leg side.
On a length, outside off, left alone by Abid Ali.
A touch fuller, on off, angling in. Abid Ali stays solid in his defence.
Length ball, on middle. Abid Ali clips it to deep square leg. He crosses ends.

Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Ebadot Hossain appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. Clear inside edge on that one and Bangladesh do not opt for a review and rightly so.
Flatter ball, coming in with the arm. Abid Ali pushes it to mid on. There is a fumble by the fielder there which allows the batters to take a single.
On middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it out to the off side.
On middle, kept out by Abdullah Shafique.
Full and on off, defended solidly.
Sliding in, on leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on off. Abid Ali covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball, on middle. Abid Ali mistimes his pull to mid-wicket.
Short again from Ebadot Hossain, on middle. This time Abid Ali sways away from the line and ducks under it.
Short yet again, on leg. Ducked underneath.
Fuller this time, on off. Ali drives it towards covers.

FOUR! A good way to end the over! Back of a length, on off. Abid Ali punches it off the back foot through covers. Two fielders give it a chase but there's no stopping that. Abid Ali continues on his merry way.
Full and on leg, clipped to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali presses forward and blocks.
On off, blocked on the off side.
Given some loop, on off. Ali is solid in his defence.
Full and on off, driven to mid off.
Outside off, cut to point.
Good-length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it with a dead bat.
On a length, on off. AS defends it watchfully on the leg side.
Length ball, going down leg. Abdullah Shafique leaves it untouched.
On a good length, on middle. Abdullah Shafique is not troubled by that line and easily blocks it from the crease.
Back of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique crunches it off the back foot towards cover-point. Only for a single though.
On a length, on middle. Ali turns this one to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique taps it to point.
Abdullah Shafique defends it well to the off side off the back foot.
Full and on middle, blocked.
On the pads, blocked to the leg side.
Drifting down leg, Abdullah Shafique gets low and sweeps it to fine leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto gives it a chase and dives to stop the ball. Saves a run for his team.
Full and around off, driven to sweeper cover for a run.
Starts with a fuller delivery, on middle, Ali nudges this to mid-wicket.
Abid Ali again flicks this fuller delivery to the mid-wicket fielder.
Short of a length, around off, punched to the leg side.
Goes fuller now, on off, Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, fuller, whipped but straight to the mid on fielder.

Call is for two and they get two comfortably! Outside off, a touch shorter here, Abid Ali stands back and pumps this through covers. Calls for two as soon as he hit it and they complete it with ease. 100 up for the visitors!
Loopy, around off, pushed to covers, who half-stops this. They want one but they do not go for it.
FOUR! Confident shot. This is bowled pretty full, loopy around off, Abdullah Shafique dances down and thumps this one over mid off. A couple of bounces and past the ropes.
Slower through the air, lands fuller on off, Abdullah Shafique presses forward but keeps his blade close to his body looking to defend. The ball goes past the outside edge into the keeper's mitts.
A copy of the previous delivery. On off, fuller, lands and turns away, Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but gets beaten all ends up.
On the pads, nudged to the leg side.
Quicker and on the pads, whipped through square leg for a run.
Outside off, defended out.
On middle, flicked to the mid-wicket fielder.
On a fullish length, around off, Abdullah Shafique clips this through mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Abid Ali plays this with soft hands through mid-wicket and hands the strike back to Abdullah Shafique.
Good-length on off, blocked.
Slipped down the leg side now, Abdullah Shafique looks to whip it but misses his connection.
On off, AA defends.

Turn and bounce here! Given nice flight, lands fuller around off, the ball spins away sharply and just whizzes past the attempted defense of Abid Ali. The keeper takes it and appeals but the umpire is unmoved. They do not go for the review this time. A good decision as UltraEdge later shows that there was no edge.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
It is bowled on middle, kept out.
Outside off, pushed to point.
Full on off and middle, blocked well. A testing over by Taijul Islam!
Fullish on middle, worked through square leg for one.
Abid Ali punches this full ball to the left of mid on, who shuffles across and stops the ball.
FOUR! Poor delivery. Pakistan release some pressure. Down the leg side, Abid Ali tickles this one to the fine leg fence.
On a length, on off, blocked.
On off, pushed back to Jayed, who stops it in his followthrough.
Outside off, length, played to covers.
On middle, blocked.
Floats it up, outside off, eased to the right of the bowler.
