On the pads, tucked to the fielder at square leg.
Abdullah Shafique leaps ahead to this full ball and eases this to covers.
Shorter, around off, Abdullah Shafique pushes this to covers.
Flighted, outside off, pushed to covers. Maiden for Islam!
Flatter, on off, pushed to the leg side.
Around off, tossed up, blocked.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Shorter, around off, knocked to the leg side, where the mid-wicket fielder dives to his right and stops the ball.
Outside off, fuller, eased to covers.
Maiden for Hasan on his new spell! On off, blocked.
Loopy ball, on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle, kept out to the off side.
Full and on off, driven to long off for a run.
Flighted ball, on off. Ali blocks it off the front foot.
Short and on middle, cut away to covers off the back foot.
Tosses it up, on off. Abid Ali is solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the leg side.
Full and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique stays solid in his defence.
Full and around off, bunted down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Abid Ali eases it to long on for a single.
Slider, on middle. Abid Ali cuts it very late towards point.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Lot of turn there! Tosses it up, outside off, turning away. Abid Ali looks to push it to the off side but misses by a mile. Even he is surprised with that much amount of turn.
An arm ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Outside off, Abid Ali hangs back and cuts it to deep backward point for a couple of runs.
Quicker, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Very full, on middle, clipped to short leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Shafique turns this to mid-wicket.
On the pads, tucked to square leg. Abdullah Shafique calls for a single but is sent back by Abid Ali.
On middle, kept out.
Full, on off. Abdullah Shafique drives it towards mid off. This time Abid Ali calls for a single but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique.
Tossed up, on middle. Abdullah Shafique is solid in his defence.
Floated ball, on off. Abid Ali plays it on the off side.
This is pushed towards covers.
SIX! That came against the run of play! Loopy ball, on middle. Abid Ali gets low and slog-sweeps it towards long on for a maximum.
Good comeback from Taijul Islam! Bowls it quicker, on off. Ali defends it out.
Well outside off, left alone.
Flatter ball, on middle. Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Oh! That looked pretty close! Loopy ball, turning in on leg. Abid Ali prods and awkwardly tucks it past short leg for a single.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends.
Full and on middle, drilled down to long on for a run.
On middle, kept out.
Given some air, on off. Abdullah Shafique drives it to long off for a single.
On off, blocked out off the back foot.
Tossed up, outside off. Abid Ali punches it through covers for one.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Pulls his length back, on middle. Abdullah Shafique punches it back to the bowler. Mominul Haque misfields but the batters decide against the single.
On off, pushed towards covers.
Full and on off, Abid Ali looks to defend but gets an inside edge.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Floats it up, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Abid Ali hangs back and cuts it towards deep backward point for three runs.
On middle, kept out.
Lot of turn there! Tossed it up, outside off, spins a huge mile. Abid Ali leaves it alone.
Spinning away again, outside off. Abid Ali cut it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique rocks back and cuts it to sweeper cover and crosses over.
An arm ball, outside off. Abid Ali hangs back for a late punch towards covers.
On off, Abid Ali pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, around off, Ali defends it well.
Darted on middle and leg, knocked to square leg.
Darted on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Loopy on middle, nurdled to the mid-wicket fielder.
Goes fuller, but down leg, AS tickles this one through square leg for one.
Tossed up, around off, eased to covers for a single.
Full on off, defended back to the bowler.
Around middle and off, kept out.
Around off, tossed up, pushed through covers for a single.

SIX! Fifty for Abdullah Shafique! His debut and he already gets a 50! What a way to get to the landmark as well. This is tossed up, fuller around off, Abdullah Shafique shimmies down and tonks this one over the bowler's head for a massive biggie. A brilliant knock and he will want to turn this into a big, big score.
On off, defended out.
Shorter, outside off, dabbed to point.
Floated, on off, kept out.
Short, on the body, turned to square leg. Ali wants a run but is sent back.
Short outside off, defended back on the deck.
Around off, fuller, AA blocks.
On middle, solid defense from Ali.
Shortish and on middle, played to the mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length, around off, angling in, Abdullah Shafique defends it to the off side.
Around off, AS blocks this to mid on.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique's flick finds mid-wicket.
Outside off on a length, coming in, AS defends.
Around off, fuller in length, solid in defense, is Abdullah Shafique.
On off, kept out.
On off, on a length, blocked.
Abid Ali punches this to the mid on fielder.
A bumper on middle and leg, ducked under by Abid.
Short of a length, outside off, punched off the back foot to covers.
Outside off, pushed gently through covers for a run.
Serves a well-directed short ball, outside off, Abdullah Shafique sits under this one.
Taijul Islam starts with a loopy ball, on off. Abid Ali rocks back and punches it through covers for a single.
Full, given some flight, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and defends it on the off side.
On off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards point.
Some turn there! Floated dlivery, on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Bangladesh strike straightaway in the first over of Day 3! Taijul Islam finally provides them with the breakthrough. An arm ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique stays on the back foot and looks to cut it late. The ball hits the pad first and then hits the bat. Taijul Islam appeals for an lbw and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Abdullah Shafique thinks about taking a review but decides against it. Just the start Bangladesh would have hoped for.

OUT! LBW! Jubilation for Bangladesh! Taijul Islam has struck twice and they are coming back strongly here. Taijul Islam tosses this one up nicely, on middle, turning away from the batter. Azhar Ali looks to defend but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Huge shout from Taijul Islam and Co. but the umpire nods his head. It looked plumb and Bangladesh opts for a review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows three reds. Bangladesh are in delight and Azhar Ali will have to walk back for a golden duck. Taijul Islam will be on a hat-trick in his next over.
Short of a length, outside off. Abid Ali punches it towards covers.
On a good length, outside off. Abid Ali leans and defends it out.
Length ball, with a hint of inward movement. Abid Ali is slightly caught at the crease but does well to block it out.
Fuller in length, coming back in, on off. Abid Ali looks to drive but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket.
Keeps it full, outside off. Abid Ali drives it to mid off.
On a good length, on middle. Abid Ali prods across and defends it to mid on. A maiden for Ebadot Hossain!
No hat-trick! Tossses it up, on middle. Babar Azam prods and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Babar Azam pushes it towards covers.
Quicker, on middle. Babar Azam knocks it back to the bowler.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full, on off. Azam is solid in his defence.
Another maiden for Taijul Islam! Bangladesh have started strongly here. This is shortish, on off. Babar Azam prods and defends it on the off side.
Good-length ball, on middle. Abid Ali hops and defends it to mid on.
A touch fuller this time, on off. Abid Ali pushes it towards covers.
On a length, outside off. Abid Ali looks to push it on the off side. The ball goes off the outside edge towards gully.
On a good length, coming back in, on off. Ali punches it towards covers off the back foot.
Much straighter this time, on middle. Abid Ali covers the line and watchfully knocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on middle. Blocked out. Another maiden for Bangladesh and Ebadot Hossain!
Tossed up, on middle. Azam watchfully blocks it out.
The ball kept a little low there! Shortish, on middle. Azam defends it from the crease.
Angling it on the pads, Babar Azam tucks it to deep square leg for three runs.
Full and on off, Abid Ali is solid in his defence.
Quicker this time, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Risky shot that! Loopy ball, on middle. Abid Ali hangs back and cuts it towards backward point.
Back of a length, on off. Azam fends it back to the bowler.
On a good length, outside off. Azam watches it sail through.
Good-length ball, outside off. Azam pushes it towards covers.
Good-length ball, close to off stump. Babar Azam defends it on the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Babar Azam punches it towards covers.
Fuller in length, on off. Babar Azam pushes it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Fuller and slower in the air, on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Arm ball this time on middle. Abid plays it off the back foot to short leg.
Shortens his length around off. Abid pushes it off the back foot towards sweeper covers for a single.
Fuller on off. Babar defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up around off. Babar gets forward and blocks it.
Another loopy delivery on off. Watchfully blocked out by Babar.
Good-length delivery outside off. Abid leaves it alone.
Fuller length this time outside off. Driven straight to the cover fielder.
On a length, on the pads. Flicked to square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Babar Azam looks to push it off the front foot. Goes off the bottom half of the blade to gully.
Length ball, around off. Babar Azam defends this off the front foot.
On a length again, around off. Babar Azam looks to defend this off the front foot but gets and inside edge onto his pads.
Quicker and flatter around middle. Defended to the on side off the back foot.
Fuller on middle. Abid Ali paddle sweeps it to the fine leg region for a couple.
Shorter length around off. Pushed off the back foot to covers.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Abid Ali defends this comfortably to the on side.
Another quicker delivery on middle. Abid Ali blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
On a length, on the pads. Babar Azam clips it to mid-wicket for a couple.
On a length, outside off. Babar Azam punches it off the back foot to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Another length delivery but wider outside off. Babar Azam comfortably lets it go.
On a length again, outside off. Babar Azam leaves it.
Fuller delivery around off. Babar Azam gets forward and defends it solidly.

CENTURY! Abid Ali gets to his fourth Test ton! What a knock he has played. Taijul Islam bowls a loopy ball, on middle and leg. Abid Ali goes back and clips it to deep square leg. He comes back for the second run and gets it comfortably. He removes his helmet and soaks in the applause from the dressing room. A pat on the back from Babar Azam as well. He has played an exceptional knock and would look to continue to bat on.
Shorter length on off. Abid Ali cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Fuller on middle. Babar Azam drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up on off. Babar Azam skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up around leg. Babar Azam looks to turn it onto the on side. But gets a leading edge. The ball is in the air but way short of the bowler.
Fuller on off. Babar Azam defends this off the front foot.
Shorter length around off. Abid Ali pushes it off the back foot to sweeper cover.
Nicely tossed up around off. Babar Azam looks to defend but gets the inside half of his blade onto the on side.
Shorter length on middle. Babar Azam works it away to the on side.
Tossed up on middle. Blocked away off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off. Babar Azam drives it to long on for a single.
Shorter length on off. Abid Ali pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Abid Ali sweeps but gets the top edge as the ball turns away. The ball goes high in the air towards the vacant fine leg area and he gets a couple.
Shorter length on off. Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Arm ball angling into middle and leg. Abid Ali looks to work it away but gets rapped up on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Fuller on off. Abid Ali pushes it to left of cover for a single.
Shorter length around off. Babar Azam makes room and cuts it to the cover fielder.
Tossed up, around off. Babar Azam blocks it out comfortably
Tossed up, outside off. Abid Ali punches it towards covers for a single.
On the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on off. Babar Azam presses forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked on the leg side.
On middle, blocked out from the crease.
Full, on off. Azam pats it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
On the pads, Abid Ali looks to tuck it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early. Gets a leading edge but well short of silly point.
Loopy ball, on off. Abid Ali blocks it out.
Outside off, pushed to point.
Floats it up, on off. Ali is solid in his defence.
Drops his length back, on middle. Ali blocks that one from the crease.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam is solid in his defence.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tosses it up, on middle. Babar Azam camps back and steers it through covers. The ball races away to the boundary.
Full and around off, Azam defends it solidly.

OUT! TIMBER! What a delivery from Mehidy Hasan! Right through the defences of Babar Azam. This was a lot quicker, on off, straightens up after landing. Babar Azam stays on the back foot and tries to push it to the off side but the ball doesn't turn. It beats the outside edge of Babar Azam and rattles the off stump. Babar Azam cannot believe it. Mehidy Hasan runs away in delight. This has been a great start for Bangladesh. Pakistan lose their third wicket. Mehidy Hasan has given Bangladesh a huge breakthrough by scalping the Pakistani skipper.
Off the mark straightaway! Darts in full, on middle and leg. Fawad Alam knocks it to mid on for a single.
On the pads, nudged to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball, on middle. Fawad Alam gets forward and defends.
Full and on middle. Alam steps out and defends it on the off side.
Loopy ball, on off. Alam presses forward and defends it out.
On middle, watchfully blocked out.
Flatter ball, on leg. Fawad Alam pushes it past the bowler and scampers for a run.
Outside off, Abid Ali pushes it to the left of extra cover for a single.
Given some loop, on off. Ali defends it solidly.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Abid Ali gets low and paddles it to fine leg for a brace.
Quicker, on off. Ali blocks it out from the crease.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Abid Ali pushes it towards covers for a single.
Full and on leg, pushed to mid on.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali defends this tentatively off the front foot.
Fuller on the pads, Abid Ali works it to the on side.
Tossed up on middle and leg. Abid Ali works it to the on side again.

NOT OUT! Arm ball on middle by Taijul Islam. Abid Ali looks to defend it. Gets an inside edge onto his pads. Bangladesh appeal but the battter shows the bat straightaway indicating that he got an inside edge. But Bangladesh decides to go for a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows a big spike off his blade and Bangladesh loses their review. There is an excitement around the Bangladesh camp now as the spinners are getting good purchase off the pitch.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Fawad Alam gets forward and clips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Tosses it up, on off. Alam defends it out.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Outside off, cut to point.

FOUR! That's sweetly timed! A lot fuller this time from Mehidy Hasan, outside off. Fawad Alam leans onto it, opens the face of the bat and drives it through covers. There's no stopping that. A boundary!
On middle, kept out by Alam.
Shorter length around off. Abid Ali pushes it off the back foot to sweeper cover for a single.
Fuller and turing into the batter. Fawad Alam defends it to the short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another wicket for Bangladesh! Taijul Islam bowls this slower in the air on off. Gets the sharp turn into the batter. Fawad Alam fails to read the length of the ball and gets surprised by the turn. The ball hits his gloves onto the pads and loops up in the air behind the stumps. Liton Das shows superb reflexes by diving across and pouching it. Bangladesh appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They go for the review. The replays roll in and UltraEdge shows a spike on the glove. Excellent review from Bangladesh and Taijul Islam gets his third wicket. Fawad Alam has to walk back and Bangladesh are right on top now. Pakistan trail by 148 runs.
Howout: c Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Slower through the air, on off. Mohammad Rizwan defends it solidly.
Floats it up, on off. Mohammad Rizwan defends it to short cover.
An arm ball, on middle, Mohammad Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
Flatter ball, on off. Ali stays solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali drops it to the off side and takes a quick single.
Fuller on off. Mohammad Rizwan defends this out.
Quicker and flatter on off. Mohammad Rizwan gets right behind it and blocks it.
Tossed up around off. Mohammad Rizwan defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up on off again. Rizwan blocks it solidly.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
Shorter length around off. Abid Ali punches it to cover.
Fuller this time on off. Abid Ali blocks it out watchfully.
Quicker and flatter around leg. Abid Ali looks to sweep it but misses. An appeal from Bangladesh but it looks like it was sliding down the leg.
Quicker on off. Defended off the back foot.

FOUR! LUCKY BOUNDARY! Tossed up, on off. Abid Ali pushes forward for the defence but gets an outside edge. It brushes off the keeper's pad and goes just away from the fielder at first slip and races away towards third man for a boundary.
Fuller on off. Blocked off the front foot.
Fuller on off. Mohammad Rizwan pushes it defensively to covers.
Shorter length on off. Mohammad Rizwan moves across and defends it watchfully.
Mehidy Hasan bowls this down the leg side. Mohammad Rizwan looks to sweep it but misses. The wicketkeeper misses too and the batters steal a bye.
Fuller on middle. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
Fuller on middle. Abid Ali nudges it to the on side for a single.
Given some air, on off. Ali pushes it to point.
Shortish, outside off. Blocked out by Ali.
Full and on off, pushed to the off side.
On the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on leg. Abid Ali sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Full and on middle, kept out by Rizwan.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Ali uses his feet and defends it towards covers.
On off, nudged to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on off. Abid Ali looks to sweep but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Half-hearted appeal from Bangladesh for lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
This is knocked down to long on for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Rizwan presses forward and defends it out.
Shortish, on off. Ali punches it towards covers. He calls for a single but is sent back by Rizwan.
Around off, pushed to sweeper cover for a single this time.
Loopy ball, on leg. Rizwan clips it to mid-wicket for a run. He gets off the mark after facing 14 deliveries.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated it up, on middle. Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Full and onto the pads, tucked to short leg.
Full, on off. Rizwan stays solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, on off. Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler.
Around off, blocked out watchfully by Rizwan.
Loopy ball, on off. Rizwan looks to defend but gets an outside edge. Played it with soft hands and thus, does not carry to the first slip fielder.
On middle, defended solidly.
Sharp turn but going down the leg side. Rizwan leaves it alone.
Tossed up nicely, outside off. Ali punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Full and on middle, swept to deep square leg. Rizwan pushes hard for the second runs and gets it easily.
Flighted ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Rizwan blocks it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Tosses it up, on middle. Rizwan looks to defend but gets an outside edge to short third man.
Onto the pads, Abid Ali clips it to deep square leg for an easy single.
Loopy ball, on off. Rizwan presses forward to block.
On off, Rizwan taps it towards point for a quick single.
Floats it up, on off. Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Full and quicker, around off. Ali stays solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, outside off. Ali defends it to the off side.
Full and quicker, on off. Rizwan sweeps it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, Mohammad Rizwan defends it watchfully.
Mohammad Rizwan comes down the track and drives but finds the cover fielder. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Fired in, on leg. Rizwan works it away to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter ball, outside off. Abid Ali defends it to cover.

FOUR! Well played! Flatter and quicker, on off. Abid Ali stays back and crunches it towards deep point for a boundary. That brings up the 200 for Pakistan as well. They trail by 127 runs. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Length ball, well outside off, the ball stays a bit low. Mohammad Rizwan looks to cut but misses.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Mohammad Rizwan stands on his toes and looks to tuck but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad. Bangladesh players appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Length ball, outside off, nipping away. Mohammad Rizwan lets it sail through.
On a length, outside off, nipping away. Mohammad Rizwan leaves it for the keeper to collect to dives to his right to stop the ball.
Outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to that one.

On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Mohammad Rizwan looks to drive it on the up but misses. The ball passes through the inside half of the bat and into the keeper's mitts. A maiden for Ebadot Hossain!
On a good length, outside off, in the corridor of uncertainty. Abid Ali lets it be.
Good-length ball, on off, shaping away. Ali covers the line and blocks it from the crease.
Sprays this one down leg, Ali leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, on off. Ali punches it towards covers off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot! Too full and on the leg stump, Abid Ali wrists it through mid-wicket and fetches himself a boundary. Delightful-looking shot that!
On a good length, outside off. Abid Ali leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! What a breakthrough for Bangladesh and what a start for them post Lunch! Ebadot Hossain dishes out a good-length ball, on middle, coming back in slightly. Mohammad Rizwan comes across and looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the back pad. Ebadot Hossain knew it straightaway that it was dead plumb and appeals. The umpire takes no time raising his finger. Mohammad Rizwan consults his partner for taking a review but decides against it. Replay shows that, it was crashing onto the middle stump. Excellent start for Bangladesh post Lunch.
On a length, on off. Faheem Ashraf defends this solidly towards the off side.
Fuller this time on off. Faheem Ashraf drives it to mid off.
Short ball by Ebadot Hossain outside off. Faheem Ashraf leaves it alone. Good bowling this by Ebadot Hossain.
Fuller delivery on off. Faheem Ashraf pushes it to covers.
On the pads this time and Faheem Ashraf clips it to fine leg for a single. End of a successful over by Ebadot Hossain.
Fuller, outside off, nipping away. Faheem Ashraf ignores that one.
FOUR! Classy shot! Full again, width offered outside off, Faheem Ashraf drives it crisply through extra cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Faheem Ashraf punches it through covers for a single now.
Back of a length, on off. Ali punches it to extra cover.
On a length, on off. Ali nudges it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Ali punches it towards deep cover for a couple of runs.
Short of a length, on middle. Faheem Ashraf pulls it through mid-wicket. Pushes hard for the second run and gets it comfortably.
Good-length ball, outside off. Faheem Ashraf looks to cut but gets beaten on the outside edge. This is the length that Bangladesh pacers might want to exploit more.
On a length, on off. Ashraf defends it out.
On a good length, on middle and leg, angling in. Faheem Ashraf looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Ebadot Hossain appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Back of a length, on off. Faheem Ashraf knocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, pushed towards covers.
Given some flight, full, on middle. Abid Ali blocks it out.

DROPPED! Loopy ball, on middle. Abid Ali dances down the track and clips it to short leg. The fielder there moves to his right and almost holds onto it but drops it at the end. How costly this could prove to be for Bangladesh as it is Abid Ali who has been dropped.
Full, on off. Ali blocks it to the off side.

OUT! LBW! Bangladesh will be relieved. The dropped catch does not cost them at all. Taijul Islam is breathing fire as he bags his fourth wicket. Tosses it up nicely, on middle and leg. Abid Ali sits back and tries to steer it away but plays down the wrong line. He misses and the ball skids onto the pads. Taijul Islam appeals for an lbw and the umpire agrees. Abid Ali opts for a review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows umpire's call on wickets hitting. Pakistan will retain the review but they have lost Abid Ali. Taijul Islam gets a wicket in his very first over after Lunch and they are well on top.
Tossed up on off. Hasan Ali prods forward to defend it but gets a thick outside edge square on the off side for a single.
Fuller and slower in the air on off. Faheem Ashraf defends it off the front foot.
On a good length outside off. Hasan Ali leaves it alone.
Overpitched this time on off. Hasan Ali drives it to mid off.
BEATEN! Good-length ball around off. Hasan Ali pushes at it tentatively as the ball just misses the outside edge of his blade.
On the pads this time, Hasan Ali works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Play and a miss! Length delivery from 'round the wicket. Faheem Ashraf tries to cut it but misses.
Ohh....a yorker this time on off. Faheem Ashraf digs it out and gets the bottom part of his blades onto the pads. Bangladesh think of a review but decides against it.
FOUR! Hasan Ali wants to gets some quick runs now! Tossed up on middle. Hasan Ali gets under it and lifts this over mid on for a boundary.
SIX! Hasan Ali is not going to stop himself! Tossed up again on middle and leg. Hasan Ali plays the slog-sweep against the turn over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.

OUT! STUMPED! Gone this time! The party is over for Hasan Ali! Nicely tossed up on middle. Hasan Ali dances down the track and looks to slog it away against the turn. But misses. The ball goes back to the wicketkeeper and Liton Das behind the stumps whips the bails off as Hasan Ali tries to get back into his crease. Taijul Islam gets a five-fer and Pakistan are in real trouble now!
Howout: st Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: NOT OUT! Sajid Khan survives! An arm ball from Taijul Islam quicker angling into the batter. Sajid Khan looks to work it away but misses. Gets rapped up on the pads. Bangladesh players appeal and the umpire raises his finger. The batter goes for a review and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball is missing the stumps. The decision will be overturned and Sajid Khan stays to fight another day.
FOUR! Nice way to get off the mark! Loopy ball, outside off. Sajid Khan drives it on the up through covers for a boundary.
On off, punched towards covers.
Full and in the blockhole. Faheem Ashraf digs it out on the leg side for a single.
Fuller in length, on midde and leg. Sajid Khan covers the sticks and nudges it to mid-wicket.
That was close! Good-length ball, just over the off stump. Sajid Khan comes to play this straight but gets beaten.
Full and quick, outside off. Sajid Khan lets it be.
Good-length delivery outside off. Sajid Khan pushes at it tenatively but misses.
On a length, on off. Blocked off the front foot.
fuller on off. Faheem Ashraf pushes it to covers.
Shorter length around off. Faheem Ashraf cuts and gets a thick outside edge to the third man region for a couple.
Flatter on off. Blocked out by Faheem Ashraf.
Slower in the air, on off. Faheem Ashraf defends this off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Faheem Ashraf works it to mid-wicket.

Fuller on off. Faheem Ashraf drives it to mid off. The fielder there half stops it as the batters take a single. Then the fielder throws in a needless throw at the bowler's end and the batter take an extra run of an overthrow. Two runs in the end. Sloppy fielding there.
Ebadot Hossain bowls this down the leg side. Sajid Khan looks to get a bat on that one but is way too down the leg side.

EDGED but short of the fielder at second slip! A Good-length delivery around off. Sajid Khan pokes his bat at that one and gets a thick outside edge just short of the second slip. The fielder there fails to stop it cleanly and the batters take a single.
On a length, outside off. Faheem Ashraf punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Sajid Khan works it to mid-wicket.

OUT! BOWLED! Sajid Khan is cleaned up here! Ebadot Hossain bowls this in that channel of uncertainity in the line of the off stump. Sajid Khan looks to defend it but completely misses the line of the ball as the ball nips away a little and shatters his off stump. Another wicket for Bangladesh and Ebadot Hossain and they are all over Pakistan now.
On a length, around off. Nauman Ali taps it to point. End of a brilliant over by Ebadot Hossain.
Tossed up, outside off. Faheem Ashraf looks to drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, Faheem Ashraf eases it in front of cover for a single.
Given some flight, on off. Nauman Ali looks to drive but gets an inside edge back to the bowler.

How did that miss hitting the stumps? Loopy ball, on off. Nauman Ali looks to slog it on the leg side but misses. The ball was whiskers away from hitting the off stump. Nauman Ali is fortunate enough to still be there.
Full and on leg, blocked out.
Full and on off, pushed to point.
Short of a length, outside off. Faheem Ashraf mistimes his pull to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Faheem Ashraf flicks it to deep square leg. He pushes hard for the second run and gets it easily. Each single run is important for Pakistan now!
Back of a length, on off. Punched to covers for a single.
On a good length, on off. Nauman Ali taps it to point for a tight single.
Length ball, outside off, nipping away. Faheem Ashraf looks to push it to the off side but gets beaten.
Much straighter, on middle. Knocked back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, outside off. Ali dabs it to backward point for a run.
On off, pushed to covers.
This is eased down to mid on for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, patted back to the bowler.
Around off, blocked from the crease to the off side.
Loopy ball, on middle. Ashraf is solid in his defence.
Tossed up, on off. Faheem Ashraf blocks it out.
Full, on middle, Faheem Ashraf defends it watchfully.
FOUR! That will relieve some pressure! Loopy ball, on off. Faheem Ashraf gets low and slogs it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. 250 up for Pakistan!
On off, tapped towards covers.
Floats it up, outside off, pushed to covers.
Sliding down leg, Nauman Ali tickles it to fine leg. Long chase for the short fine leg fielder and keeps it down to a couple.
Loopy ball, on off. Nauman Ali blocks it out.
FOUR! That is a good shot! Tosses it up, on middle. Nauman Ali gets down on one knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Taijul Islam tosses it up, on middle. Nauman Ali looks to tuck it on the leg side but misses. He gets thudded on the pads. Taijul Islam appeals for an lbw and the umpire agrees. Nauman Ali is very confident of getting an inside edge and he straightaway review. UtraEdge shows a spike but the bat is very close to the pad.  The evidence isn't conclusive enough and the umpire goes with pad first. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Pakistan burn a review as well. Taijul Islam is on fire as he bags his sixth wicket.
On middle, blocked out.
Full and outside off. Shaheen Afridi hits it through covers for a couple.
Flatter and quicker on off. Faheem Ashraf defends this off the front foot.
Slower in the air on off. Faheem Ashraf pushes it to covers.
Shorter length around off. Faheem Ashraf looks to cut but fails to get the timing as the ball rolls towards the off side.
Fuller on off. Faheem Ashraf looks to drive but gets the inside half of his blade onto the turf.
Darted on middle and leg. Faheem Ashraf gets across and defends it

NOT OUT! A slider down the leg side. Faheem Ashraf looks to work it away off the back foot but misses. Gets rapped up on the pads. Bangladesh players appeal but umpire is unmoved. They take a review. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows umpire's call on wickets hitting. Bangladesh retain their review though and Faheem Ashraf survives.
Fuller and turing in. Defended to the short leg.
FOUR! GOOD SHOT! Fuller on off, Shaheen Afridi reverse-sweeps it to the third man region for a boundary.
Fuller on middle. Driven to long on for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Another boundary! On the pads, Faheem Ashraf sweeps it fine towards the fine leg region and the ball races away towards the boundary.
Fuller on off. Faheem Ashraf drives it to the cover fielder.
Nicely tossed up on off. Shaheen Afridi defends it to the off side for a quick single.
Quicker this time on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up on off. Faheem Ashraf gets forward and defends it comfortably.
Shorter length around middle and leg. Faheem Ashraf works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off. Defended off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off. Shaheen Afridi gets forward and blocks it.
Tossed up on off. Faheem Ashraf defends this onto the off side.

Slower in the air, around leg. Faheem Ashraf looks to work it away. But misses and the ball loops it the air behind stumps. No damage in the end but the bowling team got excited thinking there is a faint edge. Anyway it falls in the vacant area.
Tossed up on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Faheem Ashraf looks to work it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Slower and around off this time. Defended onto the off side.
Another flighted delivery around leg. Faheem Ashraf gets on his knees and sweeps it to backward sqaure leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Ashraf pushes it towards covers.
Around off, blocked out.
Shortish, on leg. Pushed to mid on.
Tosses it up, on off. Faheem Ashraf taps it to point. He calls for a single but is sent back by Shaheen Afridi.
Full and on off, driven to long off for a run.
Full again, on off. Shaheen Afridi presses forward and blocks it out.
On the pads, tucked to short fine leg.
Quicker, on off. Faheem Ashraf is solid in his defence.
Loopy ball, on middle. Faheem Ashraf defends it on the leg side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Faheem Ashraf looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the front pad. Taijul Islam appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Flighted, just outside off. Faheem Ashraf defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Shaheen Afridi pushes it towards covers.
Around off, blocked out.
FOUR! Crucial runs for Pakistan! Loopy ball, on middle. Shaheen Afridi gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
On off, kept out by Shaheen.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Slower through the air, on off. Shaheen Afridi defends it off the front foot.
Fuller in length, on leg. Faheem Ashraf whips it off the pads to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Oh! Nearly had him! A lovely yorker from Ebadot Hossain, on middle. Shaheen Afridi managaes to bring his bat down in time. Gets an inside edge and the ball rolls to the leg side.
Missed by a whisker! Good-length ball, around off. Shaheen Afridi goes for the hoick but fails to connect.
Sprays this one down leg. Shaheen Afridi looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length, on middle. Shaheen Afridi does well to block it out.
Loopy ball, around off, driven to long off for a single.
Tosses it up, on off. Blocked out.
On middle and leg, nudged on the leg side.
Shaheen Afridi presses forward abd blocks this one to silly point.
Full and on off, defended solidly.
Is that a dropped catch? Slightly tossed up on leg. Shaheen Afridi tries to sweep but gets a faint edge. Liton Das moves across and tries to grasp the ball but fails to do so. A tough chance though!
Full delivery on middle and leg. Faheem Ashraf pushes it to mid on.
Full ball, on off. Faheem Ashraf drills it straight to mid off.

Fuller around leg. Faheem Ashraf looks to flick it away but misses. Gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal but more on the optimistic side. Sliding down the leg side. The batters take a leg bye.
On the pads, Shaheen Afridi works it to square leg for a single.

NOT OUT! Half-volley on the pads. Shaheen Afridi looks to flick it but misses. Gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal and the umpire says no. Bangaldesh take review. But the replays show that it is pitching down the leg side. Decision stays and Bangaldesh lose their review.
On a length, on off. Faheem Ashraf punches it to mid off.
On off, blocked out.
This is kept out by Shaheen Afridi.
Outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Slightly short, outside off. Punched towards covers.
Quicker, outside off. Shaheen Afridi knocks it down to the pitch.
Full, on middle. Shaheen Afridi pushes it back to the bowler.
SIX! What a shot! Tossed up on off, Faheem Ashraf skips down the track and smashes it straight over the bowler's head for a biggie.
Fuller on off. Faheem Ashraf blocks this off the front foot.
A touch shorter around off. Faheem Ashraf pushes it off the back foot to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! It's all over! Taijul Islam bags his seventh wicket and is delighted and so are the other Bangladesh  players. Tossed up delivery around leg. Faheem Ashraf looks to sweep but gets a faint edge and Liton Das behind the stumps moves across quickly. He somehow manages to pouch the ball between his legs. A good innings by Faheem Ashraf comes to an end and Bangladesh after the first innings are leading by 44 runs.
Howout: c Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Shaheen Afridi starts with a good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Shadman Islam leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, shaping away, outside off. Shadman Islam shoulders arms to that one.
Good-length ball, on middle, little bit of away movement this time. Shadman Islam covers the sticks and blocks it to the off side.

That's a ripper from Shaheen Afridi! Quality fast bowling this! For a moment, they wanted to go upstairs. Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Shadman Islam looks to defend but gets all squared up. The ball zips past the outside edge and Mohammad Rizwan dives to his right to collect the ball.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
A maiden to begin with! On a good length, shaping away from off. Shadman Islam lets it be.
Lenght ball, outside off. Saif Hassan lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Width on offer, outside off. Saif Hassan reaches out for it. He slices it over point for a boundary. Open his account in style.
FOUR! Make that two in a row! That is not a great delivery by all means. Bowls it on the pads, Saif Hassan times his flick to perfection. The ball races away to deep mid-wicket.
On a length, down leg. Saif Hassan misses out his glance.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Saif Hassan nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and wide, outside off. Saif Hassan leaves it alone.
Sprays this one down leg, Shadman Islam tries to tuck it away but fails to connect.
Touch fuller, on off. Shadman Islam knocks it towardscovers. The fielder from mid off was quick enough to cut it off. A single taken.
On a good length, outside off. Left alone by Hassan.
Good-length ball, in the channel, outside off. Saif Hassan watches the ball closely and lets it go.
Fuller in length this time, outside off. Saif Hassan looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge. The ball rolls to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, down the leg side. Shadman Islam is not troubled by that line as he leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Saif Hassan pushes it to the off side.

FOUR! Lucky runs! Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Saif Hassan was caught in two minds there as he first tries to defend but then raises his blade. However, the ball goes off the lower part of the blade through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Saif Hassan stands tall and defends it down.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.
On a length, around off. Saif Hassan knocks it in front of cover.
Good-length ball, outside off. Saif Hassan lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, around off. Shadman Islam leaves it alone.
Good-length again, around off. Shadman Islam leaves it.

OUT! LBW! Shaheen Afridi gets the first breakthrough! On a length, nipping into the batter. He looks to clip it away but misses. Gets hit on the pads and Shaheen Afridi makes a loud appeal. The umpire raises his finger but Shadman Islam decides to take a review. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that it is  hitting the leg stump marginally and it's an umpire's call. So the decision stays and Bangladesh lose their first wicket!
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Najmul Hossain Shanto  has a poke at it but gets beaten. Lets it through for the keeper very late.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shaheen Afridi is on a roll here! This is a classic Test match dismissal for a left-arm pacer. Bowls it right in the corridor of uncertainty, shaping away. Najmul Hossain Shanto pokes at it and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies towards first slip where Abdullah Shafique takes a sharp low catch. Shaheen Afridi has two in this over and Bangladesh in early trouble. The skipper, Mominul Haque walks out to bat now.
Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Almost had another! Bangs this one short, outside off. Mominul Haque looks to fend it away but gets an outside edge. The ball drops just short of the fielder at third slip. A double wicket maiden for Shaheen Afridi.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Saif Hassan drives it to mid on.
Short of a length, outside off. Saif Hassan tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Pitched up, on off. Saif Hassan knocks it to mid off.
Good-length delivery outside off. Saif Hassan decides to leave it alone.

Ohhh...just short of the point fielder! A sharp bouncer on off. Saif Hassan is completely surprised by the bounce and pace and just pokes his bat at that one. The ball loops in the air towards the point fielder but just short  of him as he dives forward.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bangladesh 15-3 now! Pakistani pacers are on a song here. Hasan Ali serves a length ball, onto the pads. Mominul Haque hangs back, hops and clips it with a slightly closed bat face to short mid-wicket. Azhar Ali dives in front and manages to grab it inches above the ground.
Howout: c Azhar Ali b Hasan Ali

Commentary: Around off, Saif Hassan gets beaten on his defence.
Short and quick on leg. Saif Hassan hops and misses out on his glance.
On a good length, outside off. Saif Hassan lets it through to the keeper.
Short and quick, around off. Saif Hassan lets it be.
Back of a length, on off. Saif Hassan looks to drive but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls to the leg side.
On a good length, on middle and leg. Saif Hassan defends it from the crease.
On a length, outside off. Swinging away and Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Full ball, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim defends this watchfully off the front foot towards the on side.
Length delivery on the pads. Mushfiqur Rahim works it to square leg for a single.
Shorter length this time, on off. Saif Hassan defends this off the back foot.
On a length, around off. Saif Hassan pushes it off the back foot towards the point fielder.
A good short ball again, on off. Saif Hassan rides the bounce and defends this off the back foot with soft hands towards the off side.
Full and swinging into the batter. Mushfiqur Rahim works it to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it comfortably.
Shaheen Afridi goes 'round the wicket now and bowls a length delivery on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim gets his bat down in time and gets the inside half of his blade towards fine leg for a single.
Ohhh...just short of the point fielder! Back of a length, around off. Saif Hassan defends it aerially towards the point fielder. But the ball falls just short of the forward diving fielder.
Back of a length, outside off. Saif Hassan punches this off the back foot through covers. He gets three runs as the fielder running from the ring cuts it off.
Back of a length, on off. Mushfiqur Rahim gets across and nudges it to mid on.
Fuller on off. Saif Hassan drives it powerfully but hits it directly to Babar Azam at silly point. He has hurt his leg there but nothing serious.

Short ball on off. Saif Hassan pulls it aerailly but short of  the deep square leg fielder. Single taken. Babar Azam is not happy with the effor there. He suggests to Faheem Ashraf that he should have come forward and attempted the catch.
Full ball, on off. Defended off the front foot.
Fuller delivery again, on off. Mushfiqur Rahim gets forward and blocks it solidly towards the off side.

FOUR! Mushfiqur Rahim looks like a class apart! Back of a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim rides the bounce and guides it through the vacant third man region for a boundary. Nice placement and and technique shown by the senior batter.
Short delivery on off. Mushfiqur Rahim ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Saif Hassan departs! This is pretty much identical to the way he got out in the first innings! A Sharp bouncer from 'round the wicket by Shaheen Afridi angling into Saif Hassan. He is completely out of shape as he looks to defend it. The ball takes the top of his blade and loops in the air towards the bowler. Shaheen Afridi takes an easy catch off his own bowling on the followthrough and Bangladesh are four down now.
Short ball, on middle. Yasir Ali sits under it.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Yasir Ali pushes it towards off side.
Another well-directed bouncer, on middle. Yasir Ali sways away from the line and ducks underneath.
Full and outside off, Yasir Ali leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Yasir Ali presses forward and blocks it out.
Drifting down the leg side. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to clip it but misses as the ball is way down the leg side.
On a length, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim defends this onto the on side.
On the pads, length ball. Mushfiqur Rahim glances it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, on off. Yasir Ali defends this off the back foot.
On a length, on middle and leg. Yasir Ali works it to the mid-wicket region but Abid Ali runs across and dives to stop it.
Fuller on middle and leg. Yasir Ali clips it to short mid-wicket.
Starts with a loopy ball, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out.
Shortish, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim punches it off the back foot through covers for a single.
Full and on middle, kept out.
This is blocked out by Yasir Ali.
On off, punched towards covers off the back foot.
Sharp turn there! Tossed up nicely, on off. Yasir Ali presses forward to defend but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Length ball, on leg. Clipped to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Faheem Ashraf errs in his line and bowls it down leg. Yasir Ali flicks it off the wrists to deep square leg for a boundary. That will give him some confidence.
On a length, on off. Ali blocks it out off the front foot.
On middle, Yasir Ali looks to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali tucks it on the leg side with soft hands.
Good-length ball on off. Yasir Ali clips it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim pokes it with spin to point.
Loopy ball, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim gets low and sweeps it to fine leg. Hasan Ali slides in and dives to stop the ball. Saves a run for his team.
Full and on middle, blocked out watchfully.
Full and on off, Yasir Ali defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed up, outside off. Yasir Ali eases it towards cover.
Angling in with the arm, on leg. Yasir Ali stands tall and wrists it through mid-wicket for three runs.
On a length, on off. Pushed towards covers.
Fuller in length, on middle. Yasir Ali covers the sticks and defends it with a dead bat.
This is clipped to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Ali blocks it from the crease.
On off, pushed towards covers.
Back of a length, on off. Ali defends it towards covers.
Given some loop, on off. Mushfiqur Rahim prods and defends.

NOT OUT! Nauman Ali bowls a loopy ball, on middle, turning away from the batter. Mushfiqur Rahim puts a good stride forward to defend but misses. He gets hit on the back pad. Nauman Ali appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. He is very much convinced and convinces Babar Azam to go for the reivew. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing. Pakistan lose their review.
Touch too full, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out.
In-angler, Mushfiqur Rahim stays solid in his defence.
Mushfiqur Rahim goes back and tucks it to short leg.

Ohhh! There was hardly any bounce there! Nauman Ali bowls it on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim hangs back and looks to flick but misses. The ball goes through and hits Mohammad Rizwan's pads and nearly deflects onto the stumps.
Shorter length, on off. Yasir Ali pushes it off the back foot to long on for a single.
Fuller on off. Mushfiqur Rahim plays it back to the bowler.
Quicker and turning into the batter. Mushfiqur Rahim defends this off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim works it away to the on side.
Fuller and slower in the air again, on middle. Turned away to short mid-wicket.
Turning into the leg stump. Mushfiqur Rahim works it off the back foot to short fine leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Yasir Ali defends this off the front foot.
An arm ball, on middle. Yasir Ali gets back and blocks it.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Yasir Ali drives it crisply to covers. Abdullah Shafique at covers does well and stops it with a dive.
Angling and quicker into the pads. Yasir Ali defends this onto the on side.
Tossed up on middle. Yasir Ali gets forward and blocks it right under his eyes.
Another loopy delivery on middle and leg. Yasir Ali gets forward and defends. Gets the inside half of his blade towards the on side.
FOUR! A boundary to start the day! Half-volley on the pads, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads again, Mushfiqur Rahim works it to the square leg fielder.

OUT! BOWLED! Mushfiqur Rahim is gone! Big wicket for Pakistan! Good-length delivery around off. Mushfiqur Rahim decides to leave it alone at the last moment and the ball nips in sharply to uproot Mushfiqur Rahim's off stump. This is a big moment in the game and Bangladesh are on the back foot straightaway. Pakistan have an opening here and they would like to seize this opportunity.
Good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Liton Das covers the sticks and defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball, on off. Liton Das pushes at it tentatively. He gets an inside edge and the ball rolls to the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Liton Das gets forward and taps it behind point for a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, on middle, straightens up after pitching. Yasir Ali defends it from the crease.
Fuller this time, on off. Yasir Ali drives it towards point. Sajid Khan dives to his right and stops the ball.
On a good length, on off. Yasir Ali defends it down onto the pitch.
BYES! That one stays low! Fuller, outside off. Yasir Ali shoulders arms to that one. Mohammad Rizwan fails to collect the ball. It goes through the gloves to third man and the batters steal a bye.
On a good length, on off. Liton Das stands tall and blocks it to the off side.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. Liton Das taps it towards covers.
On a length, angling into the batter. Yasir Ali defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
Fuller in length, on off. Yasir Ali drives but straight to mid off.
On a length, on off. Yasir Ali defends it towards covers.
On a length, on leg. Yasir Ali looks to tuck but gets hit on the pads. Stifled appeal from Pakistan but the umpire says no.
Fuller in length, outside off. Yasir Ali drives it towards covers for a single.
Fantastic delivery! A yorker, on middle. Liton Das jams it out onto the turf.
Good-length ball, outside off, hint of away movement. Yasir Ali shoulders arms to that one.
Tad fuller this time, outside off. Yasir Ali lunges forward and defends it towards covers.
On a good length, on off. Yasir Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on off. Yasir Ali defends it solidly from the crease.

Unplayable! Full and outside off, sheer pace from Shaheen Afridi! Yasir Ali is caught at the crease. No feet movement from him. He is late to bring his bat down and the ball zips past the outside edge.
A bumper now, on middle. Yasir Ali sways away from the line. A maiden for Shaheen Afridi!
Good-length ball, on middle. Liton Das shimmies down and defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length, on off. Liton Das punches it to point.

FOUR! Nice looking shot that! Good-length ball, on middle. Liton Das presents the fulll face of the bat and punches it towards mid on. The fielder there dives to his left but fails to stop the ball. The mid off fielder gives it a chase and pushes the ball back inside the ropes. But the replay shows he has touched the cushions while doing so. A boundary!
On a length, on off, dabbed to point for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Yasir Ali pushes it towards covers.
Very full and outside off. Yasir Ali shuffles across and knocks it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Liton Das knocks it towards mid off.
Shortish, on off. Liton Das punches it off the back foot through covers for a run.
Quicker and flatter, around middle. Yasir Ali defends it towards covers.
Full and on off, Yasir Ali pressed forward and blocks it out.
Outside off, punched towards extra cover.
A direct hit and Yasir Ali was a goner! This was flatter, on middle. Yasir Ali nudges it to mid on for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
FOUR! SHOT! Back of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali punches this off the backfoot through point for a boundary. Nice timing and placement.
On a length, on off. Yasir Ali blocks it out.
Full delivery this time on middle. Yasir Ali drives this firmly to mid on.
On a length, on off. Yasir Ali blocks this off the front foot right under his eyes.
Half-volley on the pads. Yasir Ali flicks it little aerially towards mid-wicket for a couple.

FOUR! What a delivery! Lucky boundary for Yasir Ali! Good-length delivery on off. Yasir Ali looks to defend this off the front foot but the ball nips in sharply and Yasir Ali gets the inside edge of his blade past the leg stump towards the fine leg fence. A boundary!
Fuller on middle. Liton Das blocks it out.
Flatter and shorter on middle. Liton Das defends this off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle. Liton Das defends this tentatively just short of the short leg fielder.

MISSED STUMPING! Nicely flighted delivery around leg. Liton Das dances down the track and looks to slog it away but misses. Mohammad Rizwan behind the stumps fails to collect the ball and misses a stumping chance as the ball hits his pads and deflects away. A life for Liton Das!
Shorter on the pads, tucked to backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nice batting this by Yasir Ali! Fuller on middle. Yasir Ali backs away and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, on leg, Liton Das looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Just uses the pace of the bowler there! Back of a length, on off. Liton Das opens the face of the bar and guides it towards deep backward point for a boundary.
Short of a length, on leg. Liton Das nudges it to short mid-wicket for a sharp single.
On a length, on off. Yasir Ali plays it to mid on.
Fuller, on middle, angling in. Yasir Ali flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Nicely played! Wrong line from Shaheen Afridi. Bowls it down leg, Yasir Ali just helps it on its way to the fine leg fence to collect a boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Liton Das defends this onto the on side.
Shorter length around off. Liton Das cuts it to the point fielder.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Liton Das blocks it off the back foot.
Darted on the pads this time. Liton Das looks to work it away but gets an inside egde onto the pads. The ball drops just short of short leg.
On the pads again. Liton Das works it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Another beautiful cover drive by Yasir Ali. Tossed up on off. Yasir Ali leans forward and drives it crisply again through the covers in the gap for a boundary.
Shaheen Afridi bowls this from'round the wicket and short angling into the body. Liton Das ducks under it.
Another shorter length, on the body. Liton Das rides the bounce and defends it comfortably onto the turf.
On the pads this time. Liton Das flicks it to square leg for a single.
A good bouncer again, angling into the body. Yasir Ali ducks under it.

Ouch.. Yasir Ali has been hit on the helmet here! A short ball again, well targeted into the body. Yasir Ali tries to duck under it but doesn't keep his eyes on the ball. The ball doesn't bounce as much as he expected and the ball hits his helmet. He is in little pain here and the physios come in for mandatory concussion test. He is fine and ready to go.
A short ball again with same angle into the body from 'round the wicket. Yasir Ali ducks under it comfortably this time.
Fuller and slower in the air, on the pads. Tucked away to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Yasir Ali drives it to mid off.
Flatter and quicker around leg. Yasir Ali works it to backward square leg for a single.
Nicely tossed up this time on middle. Liton Das defends this out off the front foot.
Another arm ball, on the pads. Liton Das comfortably clips it to fine leg for a single.
Shorter length this time, around off. Yasir Ali punches this off the back foot to deep covers for a single
On a length, going down leg. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
On a good length, on leg. Mehidy Hasan hops and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off, angling away. Mehidy Hasan taps it to point.

Short of a length, outside off, angling away, Mehidy Hasan shoulders arms but the ball keeps a little low. It goes off the bottom half of the blade but fortunately for Mehidy Hasan, it does not carry to the keeper.
Length delivery, outside off. Mehidy Hasan pokes at it with soft hands. The ball goes towards gully.
On a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out from the crease.
FOUR! Positive intent from the batsman! Welcomes Sajid Khan with a boundary straightaway! Loopy ball, on middle. Liton Das shimmies down and smacks it towards long off for a boundary.
On off, kept out by Das.
Tossed up, on off. Liton Das plays it with spin and tucks it to short leg.
Floats it up, on middle, tucked on the leg side.
Full and on off, drilled to mid on for a single.
Mehidy Hasan prods and eases the full ball to long on to retain the strike.
Starts off with a loosener, down the leg side. Mehidy Hasan looks to flick but misses.
Fuller in length, on off. Mehidy Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan pushes it aerially to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Hasan defends it to short mid-wicket.

Length ball, on leg. Mehidy Hasan trickles it to fine leg. Hasan Ali from deep square leg runs across and dives to stop the ball. Saves two runs for his team. The third umpire checks whether Hasan Ali touched his legs on the ropes while collecting the ball back but looks good. Two runs given.
Short of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan gets behind the line and blocks it from the crease.
Loopy ball, on leg. Liton Das tickles it to fine leg for a couple of runs. 100 up for Bangladesh as well!
On middle and leg. Das nudges it to mid-wicket for a run.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tosses it up, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floats it up, on off. Mehidy Hasan gets low and sweeps it but does not hit it from the middle of the bat. The ball drops to square leg.
Flighted ball, outside off. Mehidy Hasan pats it to the off side.
Fuller on middle. Liton Das drives it straight to the mid on fielder
Full again on middle and leg. Liton Das punches it again to mid on.
Overpitched on the pads. Liton Das clips it to square leg.
On a length, on off. Liton Das blocks it out off the front foot towards the off side.
Half-volley on off. Liton Das leans forward and drives it to mid off.
On a length, on off. Liton Das blocks it out off the front foot.
Quicker on middle. Mehidy Hasan defends this off the front foot.
Slightly slower on middle. Mehidy Hasan defends this onto the on side.
Fuller on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
Shorter length around leg. Mehidy Hasan works it to backward sqaure leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Liton Das skips down the track and heaves it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.

NOT OUT! Liton Das survives! Sajid Khan bowls this slightly quicker on off and middle. Liton Das looks to work it away off the back foot. But misses. Gets rapped up on the pads and the catch is also taken at short leg. Pakistan appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Liton Das goes for a review straightaway. The replays roll in and they first check for the catch but UltraEdge shows no spike off the blade. Then they check for a possible lbw. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that ball is missing the leg stump. So Liton Das is safe as the decision will be overturned.
Short of a length, on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Sprays this one down leg, left alone.
On a length, on leg again. Mehidy Hasan clips it to backwrard square leg for a single.
Good-length ball, on middle. Das defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on middle. Liton Das uses his feet and dabs it past point. He pushes hard for the second run and makes it to the crease comfortably.
On a good length on off, Liton Das knocks it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Quicker and down the leg. Mehidy Hasan looks to nudge it but misses. Some excitement shown by Pakistan fielders but no damage done.
Tossed up on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
Shorter length, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends this off the back foot.
Another flatter and quicker ball on off. Blocked out from the crease.
Fuller on off. Mehidy Hasan defends this off the front foot.

In the air, but safe! Tossed up on off. Mehidy Hasan skips down the track and looks to slog it away. But miscues and the ball goes high in the air toward extra cover but falls in a no man's land. Single taken.
Fuller in length, with a hint of inward movement, on off Mehidy Hasan pushes it to the bower's left.
On the pads, Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
Short of a length, angled into the stumps. Mehidy Hasan hops and defends it on the leg side.
A length delivery on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends this by going deep in his crease square on the off side.
On a length again, around off. Mehidy Hasan defends this comfortably from his crease towards the off side.
On middle, slower in the air. Liton Das defends this off the back foot.
Tossed up on off. Liton Das sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted again on off. Mehidy Hasan defends this off he front foot.
Fuller on off. Mehidy Hasan pushes it to long on and gets a single.
Full again and pushed to long on for a single.
Tossed up on off. Mehidy Hasan gets forward and defends this comfortably.
Length ball, on middle. Liton Das is solid in his defence.
Length ball, on the pads. Liton Das clips it to mid-wicket.
Length again, on the pads again. Liton Das works it to deep square leg for a single this time.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Faheem Ashraf. Sprays this one down leg. Mehidy Hasan just clips it off his pads to fine leg for a boundary.
Good-length ball, on middle. Mehidy Hasan covers the line and blocks it from the crease.
Length ball, on off. Hasan taps it towards point. 5 runs from the over.
Loopy ball, on off. Liton Das comes down the wicket and hits it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Given some loop, on middle. Blocked out by Hasan.

OUT! LBW! That looked plumb straightaway. Sajid Khan tosses this one up nicely, on off, the ball turns back in sharply. Mehidy Hasan looks to defend off the back foot but misses it completely. He gets hit on the pads. Sajid Khan appeals for an lbw and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Mehidy Hasan has a quick chat with Liton Das and opts for a review. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows three danger reds and Mehidy Hasan will have to walk back to the pavilion. Sajid Khan gets an important breakthrough. The concussion substitute, Nurul Hasan walks out to bat.
Tossed up, outside off. Nurul Hasan defends it out.
That is defended out by Nurul Hasan.
Nurul Hasan comes down the pitch and blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Liton Das gets forward and defends.
Down leg, left alone.
Tossed up on middle. Liton Das drives it to the cover fielder.
Slower in ends the air, on the pads. Liton Das defends this out.
Shorter length on off. Liton Das gets back and defends it.
Tossed up on off. Liton Das gets forward and blocks it out.
Very full, outside off. Nurul Hasan drives it to mid off.
Throws this one wider, outside off. Nurul Hasan goes for the drive but gets an inside edge onto the on side.
Very full, outside off. Bunted back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Hasan blocks it out.

NOT OUT! A loud shout for caught behind from Pakistan but not given! Flighted ball, full and outside off. Nurul Hasan is drawn forward into a defense as the ball just zips through between bat and pad before just about nestling into Rizwan who somehow manages to cling on near his elbow really. Sajid Khan convinces Babar Azam to opt for the review. Nothing on UltraEdge. The third umpire checks for a possible lbw now. Ball Tracking shows that the impact was way too outside off. Pakistan lose a review and Nurul Hasan survives.
Tossed up, outside off. Pushed back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away a little. Liton Das stands on his toes and taps it to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Das pushes it towards covers.
On a good length, on middle. Liton Das gets behind the line and blocks it to the off side.
FOUR! Wonderful wrist work! Back of a length, outside off. Liton Das steers it past the diving point fielder for a boundary. Elegantly played!
Short of a length, on off. Das punches it this time to sweeper cover. There's protection in the deep and will only get a single.
Length ball, outside off. Hasan pushes it through covers for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Nurul Hasan tucks it on the leg side.
FOUR! That's a good-looking shot! Outside off, slower through the air. Nurul Hasan waits for it and cuts it to backwardpoint for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Hasan blocks it out.
FOUR! Bangladesh have started pretty well post Lunch. This is flighted, outside off. Nurul Hasan frees his arms and guides it through cover-point for another boundary.
This is pushed back to the bowler.
On off, Hasan prods and nudges it to mid on.
Short of a length, on off. Das dabs it to point.
Swing and a miss! Length ball, outside off, the ball keeps a little low. Liton Das throws the kitchen sink at it as he looks to cut. He misses out on that though.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Length ball, on leg. Liton Das clips this one to deep square leg for a boundary. Pakistan bowlers are struggling with their line and lengths. This was a poor delivery and Hasan Ali knows as he shakes his head while walking back to take the run up.
Wide outside off, Das cuts it to deep point for a run.
Fuller in length, on off. Nurul Hasan defends it towards covers.
On a length, outside off. Nurul Hasan dabs it to gully.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Full again, on off. Liton Das uses his feet to nudge it to mid-wicket.
A tough chance! Loopy ball, outside off. Liton Das takes a big stride forward and looks to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge past the diving short leg fielder for a single.
Full and outside off, Nurul Hasan plays it to cover.
Nurul Hasan eases this full ball to mid on for an easy single.
Liton Das uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and nudges it to mid-wicket.

Jaffa! Good-length delivery, around off, nipping away. Nurul Hasan gets squared up and looks to poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge. A little bit of frustration there for the bowler. That was inches close to getting the outside edge.
On a length, on off. Hasan pushes it towards point for a run.
Slightly full, outside off. Liton Das checks on his shot as he drives this one uppishly to mid off.
On a length, on off. Das guides it to point for one.
FOUR! Poor line and Afridi has to pay for it. Sprays this one on leg, Nurul Hasan simply tickles it to fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. Nurul Hasan shoulders arms to that one.
Floats it up, on off. Das works it away to square leg for a run.
Loopy ball, on off. Hasan blocks it out off the back foot.
Full and on middle, Nurul Hasan steps out and blocks it out.
Full and quicker, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle, defended to short mid-wicket.
Quicker one on off, Hasan is solid in his defence.
Bangs a short one, on middle. Liton Das comfortably ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Liton Das hops and blocks it to the leg side.
Fuller this time, outside off. Liton Das looks to push it to the off side but gets an inside edge back to the bowler. Shaheen Afridi picks the ball and mimes a throw at the batter.

FOUR! Mere push from Liton Das! Overpitched ball, outside off. Liton Das presses forward and creams the drive in front of square. Sajid Khan runs across from deep point and dives. He manages to pull the back in but it rolls back to the fence.

FIFTY! A century in the first innings follwed by a half century. What a Test he is having! Fullish ball, outside off. Liton Das guides it to deep point for a single. Nurul Hasan walks upto him to congratulate and the crowds are up on their feet as well.
Full and around off, Nurul Hasan knocks it to cover.

FIVE RUNS! Tossed up on middle. Liton Das turns it away to deep square leg. Shaheen Afridi from the deep throws a wide throw at the batter's end. Mohammad Rizwan behind the stumps fails to collect it and the ball races away to the point boundary. No one's backing up and a sloppy piece of cricket by Pakistan.
Flatter, outside off. Nurul Hasan shoulders arms.
This is pushed gently to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nurul Hasan is gone now! Tossed up on off. Nurul Hasan decides to take him on and looks to go downtown. Gets under and hits it straight down the ground but fails to get the distance as Faheem Ashraf at long on takes a fine catch. Important wicket for Pakistan and they will be looking to finish this off quickly now.
Howout: c Faheem Ashraf b Sajid Khan

Commentary: Quicker, on middle. Taijul Islam defends it back to the bowler.
That was close! Flighted ball, outside off. Taijul Islam looks to cut but almost chops the stumps as the ball dribbles beside the stumps.
Fuller, outside off, driven towards covers.
Spraying on the pads this time, Liton Das works it in the gap towards deep mid-wicket. They take three runs. Good running. Bangladesh lead by 200 runs now!
Yorker around off. Taijul Islam digs this out to short leg.
A good short ball this time, angling into the body. Taijul Islam sways away from the line.

NOT OUT! Full delivery on middle and leg. Taijul Islam looks to defend it but hits his bat on the boot. The ball hits his pads and Pakistan appeal. The umpire says no and they take a review. UltraEdge shows a flat line as the ball passes the bat. The replay rolls in and the Ball Tracker shows it is missing the stumps. So Taijul Islam survives.
Length ball, on off. Pushed square on the off side off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on leg. Das tucks it to square leg for a single.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Taijul Islam blocks this off the front foot.
Slower in the air, on off. Taijul Islam defends this off the front foot.
Shorter length, outside off. Taijul Islam looks to cut but misses as the ball turns away.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Another brilliant yorker on off. Liton Das digs it out onto the turf.

OUT! LBW! Liton Das departs after a brilliant knock and a big wicket for Pakistan this! On a length, angling into the batter from 'round the wicket. Liton Das looks to clip it away but misses as he plays all around it. The ball hits his pads and there is a huge appeal by Pakistan. The umpire raises his finger and Liton Das decides to review it. The replays rolls in and the Ball Tracker shows three reds and Liton Das has to walk back to the hut. Shaheen Afridi is the man again with the ball and he is looking a class apart from other bowlers.
Fuller in length, down leg. Abu Jayed looks to flick but misses.
Full again, on middle. Abu Jayed clips it around the corner.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one bites the dust! Shaheen Afridi gets a five-wicket haul! A dangerous bouncer from 'round the wicket angling into Abu Jayed. He has no idea how to cope with it and in the end while trying to defend gets a glove and the ball loops in the air behind the stumps. Mohammad Rizwan does the rest and takes an easy catch. Pakistan are just one wicket away now from bundling out Bangladesh. Shaheen Afridi is the man again for Pakistan who delivers under the pressure.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: A yorker on off now. Ebadot Hossain digs it out. There is some drama between Ebadot Hossain and Shaheen Afridi but nothing serious in the end.
Tossed up on off. Taijul Islam blocks this off the front foot.

OUT! STUMPED! It's all over! Sajid Khan gives a good flight on this ball around off. Taijul Islam dances down the track and looks to slog it away across the line but misses completely. The ball goes behind the stumps and Mohammad Rizwan whips the bails off as Taijul Islam is out of his crease by some margin. Third wicket for Sajid Khan and Bangladesh have been bundled out for 157 here. Pakistan need 202 to win this Test match!
Howout: st Mohammad Rizwan b Sajid Khan

Commentary: Flatter on middle to start with. Worked away to mid-wicket.
Quicker and flatter again on off. Abid Ali pushes it to covers and gets off the mark.
Quicker on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
An arm ball on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique defends this onto the on side.
Tossed up this time on off. Abdullah Shafique defends this off the front foot.
Another nice and slow delivery on off. Abdullah Shafique gets right forward to defend it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Abid Ali watches the ball closely and shoulders arms to that.

NOT OUT! Length ball, on leg. Abid Ali looks to flick but misses out on his glance. There was a sound there and Bangladesh appeal for a caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. Ebadot Hossain seems pretty confident and convinces Mominul Haque to go for the review. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. The ball brushed off the pads and carried through to the keeper. Perhaps that was the sound which interested the bowler to go for the review. The on-field decision stays and Bangladesh lose a review early on.
On a good length, around off. Abid Ali leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Abid Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller on off. Abid Ali drives it straight to the fielder at mid off.
Spraying on the pads this time. Abid Ali looks to clip it away but misses. Gets hit on the pads but going down leg.
Tossed up, around off. Abdullah Shafique meets the ball under his nose and defends.
Drifted on the pads, ticked to fine leg for a single.
Much fuller, eased to mid off.

Flighted ball, coming in with the arm, outside off. Abid Ali hangs back and nudges it through mid-wicket. The mid on fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs. Taijul Islam is not happy at all.
Quicker, outside off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards covers.
Three again! Drifting onto middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique nudges it through mid-wicket. Good running by the batters as they run three there.
Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique stands tall and plays it to mid-wicket.
On a length, on leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the leg side and takes off for a quick single.
Length ball, on middle. Abid Ali tucks it on the leg side. He calls for a single but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique.
Fuller in length, on off. Abid Ali drives it back to the bowler who does well to stop it on the followthrough.

That just took off the surface! Ebadot Hossain bangs a short ball, on middle. The ball goes swinging down the leg side. Abid Ali ducks under it. Liton Das does well to moves to his left and grab the ball.
On a length, on middle. Abid Ali knocks it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on middle. Blocked out.
On off, pushed to point.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks it out.
Full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique is solid in his defence.
FOUR! Nicely played! ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique gets down on one knee and sweeps it hard to deep square leg. There is no protection in the deep and the ball races away to the boundary.
On a good length, outside off. Abid Ali eases it towards covers.
Length ball, going down the leg side. Abid Ali leaves it alone.

Fuller in length, on off. Abid Ali drives it back to the bowler. Some aggression there by Ebadot Hossain as he collects the ball and throws it at the striker's end. That throws was absolutely needless as Abid Ali was inside the crease. Maybe just trying to get under batsman's skin.
FOUR! Wow! Abid Ali replies with his bat. Short of a length, outside off. Abid Ali rides on top of the bounce and slashes it through point for a boundary.
Overpitched ball, outside off. Abid Ali pushes it to the left of the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Abid Ali looks to cut but the ball stays a little low and sneaks underneath his blade.
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Drifting onto middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique watchfully blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the off side.
On off, Abdullah Shafique guides it to backward point.
A maiden! Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique is solid in his defence.
